text:
Really disappointed in Athens Athletics this year.  They shorted me one Jersey and two hats for youth baseball.  They told me the items would here by opening day.  Long story short, they weren't.  Nobody called, nobody apologized, no explanations were given....  I was told they had ordered me a shirt, but they no longer had the size I needed, so they ordered a different size.  Also, eventually, they told me the hats had never been ordered.

I came today and they refunded me my money that I paid them 2-3 weeks ago.  I still don't have the hats and shirts for everyone :(

resp.text: I apologize that you were not called or apologized too. These hats and jerseys are trademarked and we can’t produce them ourselves because of MLB. When the company is out of stock and tells me they can’t give me a date of when they will be there I chose to get the next size so you would have something for opening day. The hats were ordered originally and shorted from the order so they were reordered. It is not our intention at all for you not to get what you order. If I could print them myself this would not be an issue. Again I apologize for this happening!

name: Mark Hall
text: I ordered track shoes online and made the mistake of doing ground shipping instead of paying more for expedited shipping. That is my fault. The very next day, I called their customer service and asked to change to expedited shipping and pay the difference, but they told me it was too late that my shoes had already been processed and were waiting pick up for shipping. The ground shipping is supposed to be 4-6 business days. I checked today and the expected delivery date is the end of day on 4/26. That is 7 business days!! I ordered on 4/17, spoke with them on 4/18, and I still won’t have my child’s shoes for 7 business days. Their shipping is awful! It starts with UPS, and then moves to USPS, so UPS told me it doesn’t qualify for “true” tracking. It cost money, is unreliable, slow, and in the end my daughter won’t have her shoes in time for her track meet. In today’s Amazon world this company is going to get left behind with such a terrible online process. Lesson learned...the hard way!

text: I had called and talked with Zac on Monday and he was very helpful about the product and their order process. I was able to 'meet' Zac because of the product videos that are on the Wisemen Trading & Supply website.  The videos are very helpful and the product menu looks interesting.  I would never hesitate to shop at WTS.  Highly recommended

name: Sean Gill
text: While doing some research for an ax I wanted to purchase, I quite literally stumbled across your company's website and was absolutely flabbergasted at how awesome your company is.  After pulling the trigger and buying the ax I again stumbled across a YouTube video where your company outlines every single ax they sell pros cons and uses for each.  My purchase was made on a Friday and by Saturday I realized that I had never received an email regarding tracking.  believing it would probably take 8 to 10 days I wasn't terribly concerned and was content waiting until Monday to put a phone call through to see where the email was.  unfortunately I got tied up Monday and was unable to call so the call didn't happen until Tuesday.  I was totally surprised that I was able to speak with a human who immediately took my order number and plugged the tracking number in and to my absolute astonishment I was informed that my package was out for delivery.  Your company rocks Thank you.

name: Ross Lewallen
text:
Excellent service, very competent, and super easy to deal with.

A couple of months ago I drove the five-hour round trip adventure to Trek Bicycle Auburn with a friend who was purchasing a bike that they had on hand.  After talking with Ben, the manager, I was pretty impressed with the business and the level of knowledge and technical skills the staff demonstrated.  I was impressed enough that I returned last week with my Canyon for a much needed tune up and preventative maintenance.  JT and James took a lot of time with me to ensure that they fully understood what I wanted while simultaneously inputting their maintenance advice to absolutely ensure that my servicing plan was exactly what I needed.  I valued their advice because as part of my service I wanted new cables, chain, front disk brake (slight warp), and new wheel bearings.  They agreed with the cables and chain but went out of their way to straighten the disk brake and clean, inspect, and re-grease the bearings, which of course wound up being a much greater value for the money, at least on my side of the deal.  I have around 100 miles on the service and the replacement parts and the service adjustments and tuning are perfect. These small things combined with the quality of the final product earn Trek Bicycles of Auburn a great deal of trust from me, which in turn ensures that I will make that tedious drive every time I need service for my bike.  Additionally, for new bike purchases and bike accessory needs the store has many bikes on hand and nearly every accessory that one should want or need.  Thanks Team!

Thank you Ross

name: Russell Gilder
text: Super helpful and knowledgeable staff.  As well as a great location.

name: Jackie Clark
text: Everyone  was so helpful. Very knowledgeable  of all products and had recommendations. Took a lot of time with me explaining  the difference  between shoes.

name: George Sides
text:
I’ve recently retired to Orange Beach after a career in law-enforcement in Birmingham.  During my last few years on the job I sadly let my physical fitness go.  So I decided with my new life on the coast, I really needed to get back into shape.  So I came to Running Wild to get some quality running shoes.

I was greeted by Jeannie when I walked in the door.  She asked if she could help me and I asked her if she felt up to the challenge, she said “Sure.”  I explained my situation and goals, and she had me sit down and take off my shoes and socks so she could get my true size and evaluate my feet (for over/under pronation, etc).

She brought me 3 different pairs to try on, and I decided on the New Balance 860v11 which felt fantastic!  She also recommended a pair of socks which would suite me better than ordinary cotton socks which I also bought.

This was a much better experience than I’d ever had in any of the running shoe stores in Birmingham.  I can’t wait to get started training in these shoes.  And when I wear these out, I’ll definitely be coming back to see Jeannie at Running Wild!

resp.text:
George,
Welcome to the Gulf Coast and THANK YOU for shopping with us at Running Wild.  I've already passed along your kind remarks to Jeannie, she will be thrilled that you had such a positive experience.  We all look forward to hearing about your return to fitness!! Sincerely, Paul Epstein, owner.

name: Heather R. Houston
text: Went in for a new pair of running shoes & wasn't set on a specific brand. Abigail was my sales associate & did an outstanding job... i tried on at least 5 different pairs & she was very helpful & patient. I ended up getting the Brooks Glycerin very cushiony with a full toe box. Also stocked up on some nuun hydration tablets & a groovy pair of sunglasses.  Running Wild is a great store & i like supporting local small businesses.

name: Carl Reed
text: I always try to support local and the sales people are friendly and knowledgeable. A week ago, I went into the store looking for some inserts for my hiking boots. While a bit hesitant I bought some RunPro inserts for my boots given the sales person indicated  he thought they were just fine for boots and besides he added you have 30 days to try them and if you don’t like them just bring them back. Easy enough went home and found HikePro inserts on-line so I returned the “still in the box” Run Pros looking to have them credit my MasterCard. The store clerk informed me they only provide  store credit or exchanges on returns. I told her I was not made aware of this policy at the time of purchase to which she replied “sorry”. I decided not to push the matter but really let people know or better yet post a sign at the register letting people know that there are NO REFUNDS on purchased merchandise only store credit or exchanges. Disappointed.

resp.text:
Hi Carl, I apologize for the issue that you had. Somehow there is a misunderstanding with our staff member who assisted you when you returned your insoles. I’ll look up your account and  process the refund to your credit card right away. We appreciate you shopping locally and will always do the “right thing”. Paul@werunwild.com
Paul Epstein

Hello again Carl,
I'm trying to find your account so that I can process a refund to your credit card but I'm not finding anything under your name.  Please send me an email, paul@werunwild.com, or call me at our Pensacola store, 850-324-9222, so that can get this refunded to you.  Again my apologies for the misunderstanding, we've reviewed our return policy with all of our staff again.
Sincerely,
Paul

I later told him I had to go home and see if work would allow me to wear color shoes and he said no problem, no pressure.  Well I did go back and I was happy that he was there to complete my sale. text:
My podiatrist recommended this store since I needed assistance finding  suitable walking shoes. The sales person ( Owner?) at Running Wild measured my feet, observed my gait, and found the right shoes within a few minutes. And the price was in line with the stores that offer no assistance, nor the knowledge to help.
We will buy our walking shoes at Running Wild from now on. It was a very pleasant experience. Thank you!

text: Caring staff

name: Tiffany Rose
text: Be very careful when you buy from this store.  My husband bought a pair of shoes that were a bit too small for me. We let them know and they placed the order for the correct size and told us it would be the 27th of December.  It is now January 6th and still no shoes. Amazon has them available for next day shipping but they won't let us return them for anything but store credit. Not too satisfied with how my first experience with this store went. I felt they should have made an exception since they were off by two weeks (and counting) on the new pair.

resp.text:
Hi Tiffany,
I sincerely apologize for the experience that you're having with our store.  We immediately offer a refund when we have to order a size/color/style of a specific shoe that we don't have in stock and it takes longer than expected to arrive.  Somehow we did not make that clear to you and I truly apologize for that.  If you reach out directly to me at paul@werunwild.com I will process your refund immediately.  Again I apologize for the miscommunication and inconvenience.
Sincerely,
Paul Epstein

text: Excellent service!

name: Morgan Lee
text: I have never stepped foot into running wild, but I did call to get information on a pair of shoes. I have two different sized feet, I was born this way. So I simply called to ask if they had Brooks in two different sizes because the company offers this service for people like me. I told the man what I needed, a 6.5 for my right foot and a 7.5 or an 8 for the left if he didn’t mind checking for me. He asked if these were all for the same person, I responded yes, he sort of snickered when asking this, he then put me on what I guess he thought was hold but I could hear another female worker in the back say “you are so funny.” He proceeds to respond with an amused tone as to me having this difference. He picked up the phone and told me what he had, and asked a sort of belittling question... have you always had two different sized feet? “No, one shrunk over night,” is what I was thinking. I told him yes, I was born with a disability, called club foot, I didn’t try to explain I was embarrassed enough as it was and let him go. The insensitivity of these people was extremely hurtful, I didn’t ask for this but I am coping with this from birth. I have never been into running wild but I can tell you that I never will bring my business to people like this.

Highly recommend, and I'll have to check out their store in Pensacola, FL the next time I'm that way.

text: This was my first time shopping at this location. I went in with the intention of buying a new set of irons. Before I even asked a question I was asked “is your name on the list?” (There were no names on the list) I told him I wasn’t here to get fitted I just wanted to know if they had a demo I could hit a few times. He put together a club and then said we don’t have any available bays. I waited and then another gentleman came up and asked a question about club fitting and the employee that was helping me took him directly to a bay and never once said a word to me. I waited 10 more minutes and I saw bays starting to open however I couldn’t get any help. I set the club down and proceeded to walk out of the store and go directly to Edwin Watts. The employee at Edwin Watts was great and let me hit multiple different clubs and I actually ended up buying a completely different set than what I had intended. So in the span of three weeks I drop over $1,000 in the 280 store.....completely upgraded every club in my bag "m2 irons" including a new $150 bag. The cashier charged me twice for the woods....when i questioned it he acted like a jerk and started talking under his breath. I showed him on the receipt because he said "no i didn't". He asked again did i know which one I wanted because they are closing. With a smile i just said no problem I'll go somewhere else.
I will never spend another dime in this store.

Inverness Golf for me from now on.....don't waste your time or money on these rude idiots. Worst customer service I've ever!

name: Nancy Miller
text:
Wonderful customer service!!  I started a new job, recently. My “dream” job. As I learned my way around the office and got to know my co-workers, I discovered that golf is the unofficial job requirement there, lol. Having never played, I was panicked a little about pursuing this new hobby. I wandered in to the PGA Tour Superstore in Inverness.

As I browsed the store looking at the enormous selection of every kind of equipment I became so overwhelmed. Thankfully a salesperson, Drew, found me. Bless him, he was so patient as I described my predicament. He helped me find the right clubs, bag, shoes, towel, and all the other things a new golfer needs.  He was also patient with my need for things to “match” lol. Golf is an expensive pastime, but Drew made me confident in my decisions. He shared a lot of information about the local golf scene too.

I will definitively be back, and ask for Drew! It’s rare to find this kind of personal attention!  And if my co-workers can’t teach me to play well enough, I’ll be back for lessons!!

name: Evan Chandler
text:
Kenny was a great salesman and extremely helpful to someone ready to buy their first quality bike. I told him my budget and he laid out the options within +/- ~$200 of it, while explaining exactly what benefits each bike had and how (if I wanted to) spending a bit more would save me in the effort of upgrading down the road.

I never felt pressured into going over my set limit and did not feel as though I was just dealing with someone trying to make a sale. He explained where each bike sat in performance levels and related specific components to the trails I would be riding on.

He recommended a Scott bike that was equipped with an air shock and remote lockout, both of which have been fantastic to have while out in the woods.

He also explained the current technology being used in helmets, assisting me in making the correct decision for the best protection, and even deciding on what color bottle cages/pedals would fit the bike. ("these flat black cages will complement the graphics on the bike. Yeah! Those yellow pedals will definitely work with the paint!")

Will definitely shop at Cahaba Cycles again and will call Kenny when I'm ready to upgrade to a full suspension!

Again, tech refuses to take ownership of the problem and points to me. Taken my bike there twice for repairs/adjustments but nothing is ever fixed. They also take over a week to receive brake pads for bikes they stock. Why on earth do you not stock such a common part? Service guys cannot handle a task as simple as documenting my phone number. name: Michael McArdle
text: I had such an amazing experience!  What a peaceful and relaxing way to spend a Saturday. I highly recommend to anyone looking to spend a few hours on a lazy river. The multiple options to stop and rest along the way helped break up the 3 hour trip!

name: Stacey Thrasher
text: Nice folks and a nice outfitter. The put in is a little steep but there is cement steps halfway down the hill that helps. The take out is decent, also a tad bit steep trying to drag your kayak out. They do help you load and unload your yak. It was a nice float except for the water being a little low, had a few places that dragged and some rocky areas to maneuver. Overall I think it is a great float and look forward to going back again next year. Also the fishing was really great using Rooster Tail lures. Between three of us we caught about 45 fish, even caught catfish on lures. My only complaint was their porta potty, the smell was horrendous. Just don't flush until everyone in your party is done or the next person is going to gag. 😁😷

text: Sportsman's Outpost is an awesome place to go for gunsmith work (Todd), archery work (Randy) , and general hunting and shooting sports needs. Those guys are more interested in making you a return customer than making a quick sale. I, for one, appreciate that more than anything else. The pistol range (behind the store) is very professionally range mastered (Roy), and the archery course is as close to a hunting experience as possible.

They give you the simple how-to's and much more! They also have a wide selection of guns, targets, traps, etc. I try to come 2-3 times a week with my bow that I bought to practice shooting. Awesome place!

If they get more of my business, they will have to show that they can get my order right.

They also have a large walking 3d range, indoor range, and the simulated video hunting (It is a lot of fun!). You can purchase all of your outdoor needs here. Guns, Camo, Fishing Lures/supplies. Best of all the staff are all friendly, honest, and knowledgable. I like that If one of the guys doesn't know the answer to your questions, the don't b.s. you, but refer you to someone with more knowledge in the store.

name: bwcritch
text: Great place, just don’t be an idiot. Keep in mind this is a pistol range, so don’t get butt hurt if the owner asks you a few questions for his liability. I love coming here to shoot when it’s either to hot or raining outside. I’ll keep coming here.

name: Maryl Bobinger
text: My family and I have been coming here for years. We absolutely love the range, and the customer service but more importantly the time Robert takes to make sure everyone knows their guns and more importantly gun safety. My husband and I have shot guns for years but our daughter didn't. He took the time to make sure our daughter was comfortable with our guns and gun safety! We have always gotten excellent service and are impressed by Roberts attention to detail when it comes to safety. I would NEVER want to go to a place that is lackadaisical in the importance of safety and that he is willing to turn away customers that may not take gun safety seriously. He takes the time to ask questions on your abilities and your knowledge of gun safety and is not afraid of turning someone away for the safety of others. I want to know that when I am in the lane next to someone they know what they are doing and practice proper gun safety. I don't want to accidentally get shot by someone who hasn't gone through a gun safety course and been properly trained. As a gun owner you should expect nothing less from your gun range! The extra time it takes to answer a few questions should be welcomed and not taken as a sign of disrespect. Customer service here is wonderful and welcomed!!!

name: Michelle Divinagracia
text: Came here with my husband who is an ex-Marine, 5time rifle expert, 2 time pistol expert. Rifle coach. Trained hundreds of marines. But he wasn’t qualified enough to be our safety observer. And I wasn’t allowed to shoot. So we left. He was also rude and insulting. Just another guy who was too fat to become a policeman or marine and thinks he’s Rambo because he has a rusty gun collection and a shack to shoot in.

name: Nick BRANDT
text: Roberts Gun Rack is a great gun shop and range. And aside from always having a selection of handguns and rifles, Robert also has good gun knowledge and a massive amount of tools for repairs and modifications; he has helped me numerous times!  Best of all, when your done working on your gun you can step into the range to function test and practice. Great local resource!

name: Carrie Bradley
text: I have been a customer for nearly 7 years, I love the atmosphere and the owner is always so helpful. There is a lot I don't understand about firearms,  and Robert is more than willing to take the time to explain things. There's was even a couple of times I didn't have all my safety gear, and was provided what I needed to do my session.

name: alonevin boyo
text: Great place and a great guy. Know this stuff and runs a safe range! If you need or want a gun, this is the guy to talk to!

name: Ryan B
text: Found this place a couple weeks ago and I have been going every Sunday since. Robert is very knowledgeable about guns and does require that you to have high level of experience or training to shoot at his range. Good selection of guns and probably the best prices around. If he doesn't have it he will find it. Military friendly!!!

name: Jeff Caraway
text:
Robert (owner/operator) runs a good business. He will go the extra mile to help customers if he can and is honest with them if he can't (which some people may not appreciate.) I shoot there regularly and plan to continue. He has a good selection of firearms and even has some for rent.

Full disclosure; I visit regularly even if I'm not shooting, we have a lot of laughs and I learn a lot just by listening. I watched Robert spend an hour helping a seasoned citizen select and purchase a firearm last night with great patience and understanding.

name: Kent Haughton
text: I have been doing business with Robert now for 4 years......So If you are looking to buy your 1st gun or your 100th? I strongly recommend that you go see Robert. Robert cares more about fitting you with a firearm that  you can really use, more than just "taking your money". My recommendation is go shop the big box stores 1st...... then go see Robert!.. Then you will see the difference! Robert is a professional. His ethics are on point.....As for the range, it is SAFETY 1st. Robert's prices are very reasonable. His Industry knowledge is unsurpassed and remember this...Robert will "tell it like it is". What more could you want when making a purchasing decision?...Especially a firearm. I find it amusing that some people posting reviews are offended by a business man taking his business seriously. Guns are not Toys and SAFETY must come 1st!

name: Lendon Webb
text: Great place to shop and learn. Spent hours with the owner and went home with a firearm that met my needs. Will definitely buy from him in the future.

name: Thaddeus Harkins
text:
Was denied access to the range because I don't count every single round I put through each one of my pistols. Person behind the counter said 1000 round minimum with pistol was required and more than that was required if I was going to have newer shooters with me. I had some family with me that were newer shooters but all of them had experience. I knew I had shot more than 1000 but I don't know how much more because no reasonable person keeps track of that. I also indicated I've had tens of thousands of rounds through rifles but that didn't matter to the person behind the counter. Went back through my purchase history and I now see I've bought 4000 rounds of 45acp and I've used up 3 of those cases. I've put 2 cases of 1000 through my tokarev. I don't keep track of my round count. 5000 rounds through pistols over the course of the 5 years I've owned them just seems like a drop in the bucket compared to the tens of thousands rounds I put through my rifles, so I had no idea how much I've put through them.

I politely asked if he knew of a range that was open (because it was a holiday) and he proceeded to tell he wasn't going to to tell us where we could go to do something stupid, implying that any one of us would be incapable of handling a firearm safely. Extremely condescending.

name: Cal Evans
text:
This is a good, no-frills range.  We met Robert, he' is a nice person. Asked up to confirm that we had shot before, had training, and knew what we were doing. Beyond that, we filled out the form and by the time the paperwork was finished, we had a line.

The range itself it not air conditioned. So if you are going in the summer, bring a towel. :) They do have small fans mounted above each lane that help. This isn't really a complaint, just a note.

If you are used to ranges like "Nashville Armory" then this isn't that kind of range. However, it is a good range and well run.

=C=

name: Jalisa Arrington
text: I visited this business for the first time on 12/30/17 to use the gun range. Everything started off fine, but I am offended by the owner of this business. I am a reservist in the United States Air Force. The owner of this business has a  posting on his website that states that active duty military members get a $5 discount. When it was time for me to check out, I asked about the military discount and he stated to me that because I do not work with my base 5 days a week, that I am not eligible for the discount and I was charged as a civilian. I was so hurt and offended, because I took the same oath as my other brothers and sisters to protect and defend! I could get deployed today and have to fight for the very person who does not look at me as a part of the military!  I was going to let it go, but I couldn't. I called the business this afternoon and expressed how I was offended. His defense was that he was told that a reservist in the military is basically nothing but a part time position. He did offer me a full refund, but I told him that it wasn't about the money for me. He needs to do more research on his own and take care of ALL military members or no one at all! I will not be going back! If you are reserve in the military, you are just another civilian in the eyes of this business owner!! Take your business elsewhere!

name: Tevin Richey
text: Roberts Gun Rack is like my second home. He’s extremely knowledgeable, and just a all around good guy. Great range, great prices, and most important to me great service. Definitely a customer for life.

name: Melanie Noname
text: I have been to this range several times and have always had a great experience. I see some people posting about strictness but it is a gun store as well as a range and I feel like I am safe there due to the rules that have been put into place. It definitely can't be run like a car wash with just anyone coming in and out of the range area. Will be returning probably many times over!!

name: Brandon Critchfield
text: First time I came here years ago I thought the place was so-so. Since then Robert has grown on me. He offers military discounts, friendly, enjoys a good chat. Sure you may be able to find other ranges, but his is indoors and much cheaper than others nearby. Some people do't like his interview process, but its his place of business so he can do as he pleases, but honestly the interview isn't squat. I like that when isn't a big deal to turn the lights down for low light drills and he isn't hanging over you during your entire range session breathing down your neck to jump criticize your shooting like other ranges I've shot at.

name: Justin Copeland
text: Robert is a master at his craft. I highly recommend him for any firearm needs you may have. He is very knowledgeable & his prices are fair.

name: Lisa Richey
text: Great experience at Roberts Gun Rack. Wasn't sure about this place after reading previous reviews. But after visiting today I would recommend this place

name: Lisa Richey
text: Great experience at Roberts Gun Rack. Wasn't sure about this place after reading previous reviews. But after visiting today I would recommend this place

name: Rodney Williams
text: Very knowledgeable and attentive. Takes safety very serious and is patient with new users. He made sure my fiancé was comfortable before allowing her to shoot.

name: Spencer Howell
text: Great place,great prices, great selection of quality products, and is willing to educate you. He will be very blunt with you, because he cares more about safety, than if he is hurting your feelings. But he is willing to answer your questions with good information.

name: Melanie Noname
text: I have been to this range several times and have always had a great experience. I see some people posting about strictness but it is a gun store as well as a range and I feel like I am safe there due to the rules that have been put into place. It definitely can't be run like a car wash with just anyone coming in and out of the range area. Will be returning probably many times over!!

name: Jonathan Crook
text: Great man. Major knowledge with guns and safety. Offered to help improve my accuracy. GREAT CUSTOMER SERVICE!!!!!

name: Ryan Caffee
text: Excellent service if you don't want to be lied to. Robert tells it how it is, and has very very reasonable prices. He's got a return customer out of me.

name: Chris Taylor
text: The owner is very responsible and cares for the safety of his customers. As long as you have proper experience with firearms or you are with someone who has the proper experience to watch over you, you will have a good time. Love shooting my pistol here, the prices are much better than other places I’ve seen and the range is great.

name: Lady Momma
text:
The range was not bad, location was convenient for me. I am dreading the summertime. I read about the heat, but I guess I will have to drink plenty water before going and extra after.
Robert, seem to be a straightforward character and  I respect that. Some people can't handle straightforward considering the reviews. I will say get your own opinion before making a judgement. If you don't like his rules go somewhere else. I don't think there are many places.

name: Clark Griswold
text: My friends and I were looking for a place to shoot in Mobile and found Roberts Gun Rack.  Rober was very friendly and answered all our questions. Priced are good.  Military friendly.  Great way to spend a Sunday afternoon.  We will be back without a doubt.

name: chinelle hooker
text: I always have a wonderful experience at Roberts gun rack! I feel welcomed every time. This is the only range I choose to shoot at. Staff is always friendly and ready to help! Go see Roberts for all your shooting needs!

name: Brooke Carney
text: I always have a wonderful experience at Roberts gun rack! I feel welcomed every time. This is the only range I choose to shoot at. Staff is always friendly and ready to help! Go see Roberts for all your shooting needs!

name: kane blackstock
text: Great place to shoot. Has strict rules for range and it makes it very safe and comfortable.  Very nice range and very knowledgeable if you have questions.  I recommend purchase and range use there.

name: kevin pham
text: Go with experience or an experienced individual and you will have a flawless visit. Robert has a great shop as well as his personality. Very informative and knowledgeable owner. I enjoy every visit.

name: John R
text: This guy knows his stuff. Most knowledgeable gun shop owner in Mobile, he'll tell you the truth whether you like it or not. He will always try to steer you in the right direction.

name: Matthew
text: I enjoy shooting here. Robert takes safety serious and doesn't let knuckle heads in his range. Be honest with him about your experience and you'll be just fine. Try and pull the wool over his eyes and he'll see right through it.

name: Alexander Weber
text:
Great range. Very knowledgeable owner. And good selection of pistols and rifles.
Also owner prefers experienced shooters.

name: Marcus French
text: Im a u.s marine, brought the family to shoot but since some them havent shot 1,000x they were “allowed” to shoot there. Only me. So we all left. Waste of time. If they a newbies.. where else are ppl supposed to learn?

name: Oreo Jumper Guinea Pigs
text: Robert is a good guy.  Fun time today shooting target practice.   Hot as heck in that range.   Sweating like I been swimming for days.

name: Tamicheal Brown-king
text: I went for the first time today and it was the best experience at a gun range I ever visited. The staff its knowledgeable and very friendly. I love the fact its big boys rules on the range but safety first every person I met was nice I plan on going twice a month. Highly recommended.

name: albert nelson
text:
Military friendly and very knowledgeable of the law.  Indoor range is a plus.  Owner goes out of his way to help you with your gun needs.

Good selection and good prices, but will order what you need if he doesn't have it in stock

name: Hallie Hall
text: First time at a shooting range and loved it! Staff was great at educating me and giving me all the tips I needed before shooting. Will definetly be coming back!

name: Jacob S
text: I've been going to this range and have known Robert for about a year now and I have always been more than happy with my experience here.  Robert is very serious about gun safety which I view as a good thing.  If you ever have any problems with the range or with something that you have purchased in the store Robert is more than happy to do whatever is necessary to fix it.  I have been coming here fairly regularly for about a year now and I plan to continue to do so.

name: Nakiya McMillian
text: This was my first time at a shooting range. Robert was very friendly. and extremely knowledgeable. My fiance and I could not have asked for a better experience.

name: Method
text: Robert is a good dude. After reading a few of the previous reviews I went up there expecting to meet a much different character. Robert is SUPER knowledgeable and wound up selling me a shotgun. All of the people on here crying racist are probably just people he weeded out through some very simple questions on experience and safety. My only gripe is that the range was too small to fire my new shotgun, but I knew that going in. If you need experience or advice on a specific weapon purchase, I'd suggest going here and skip the mass retail outlets.

name: Shawn Hester
text: Robert and his staff were great in helping me purchase my first gun. It took a little longer than I would have expected however, with the circumstances surrounding the time of this review and my purchase, I have no hard feelings. He was very professional and very knowledgable about his merchandise. He also seemed to have no problem answering my 10+ phone calls inquiring about the arrival of my gun.He was always willing to answer my questions and give me the information I was seeking when I called. Would definitely and will go back and do business with Robert again.

name: Galen Edwards
text: I have been there several times by myself, with my wife, or with a group of friends.  The range is nice, Robert has helped me out several times when I needed stuff, his prices have always been good, and he is a genuinely nice and funny guy.  I have stopped in just to say hey sometimes and drool over the guns for sale.  I go there for everything.  If you are looking for an FFL or a range I cannot recommend him strongly enough.  As an additional bonus he helps out military personnel a lot.

name: Zachary Tomes
text: Havent been in quite some time due to lackluster and rather unappealing experiences in just the shop alone, but as a vocal consumer and someone who will live up to the "Local Guide" title, I cannot reasonably recommend this shop or range unless you absolutely have no other choice. From an owner who mindlessly goes on tangents to hear himself speak, to hilariously bad arguments with customers, on matters such as, if I remember correctly, M-14s not existing. The only marginal benefit to this place was his stock of 7.62x54r ammo crates, which were overpriced by all means, but convient. Personally, Id recommend going to Bullseye out in MS if you want to spend a fun day at the range. Great damn people and staff there, a good amount of guns to rent, and plenty of shooters more than willing to share a few rounds from their purdy pieces with others. Thats my two cents.

name: Christopher Forbus
text: I have really enjoyed my experience of buying my first handgun, and getting trained to use it properly. Robert is very professional and very concerned about gun safety. He is very knowledgeable and very helpful finding you a gun you will be happy with. I will continue to do business with Robert for as long as his doors are open.

name: Donna Counselman
text: Ladies Beware!!!! Worst experience with any business ever.  The only person that I saw working in the store never asked if he could help me and there were no other customers in the store.  I had driven over an hour with the intent of renting a gun to better determine what would work best for me, since I wasn't happy with my .38 special revolver.  After perusing the gun case I finally approached the worker (who never got off his rear I might add) for help.  I explained that I had read about the business online and wanted more information about renting guns and test firing on the gun range.  It was at this point that I was told there were new requirements to be able to use the range.  First requirement was to determine why I wanted to use the range.  Second requirement was that an individual had to have someone with them with a pistol permit, to which I replied that I did.  At this point it all started to seem like he was just making things up because he had decided he wasn't about to let me use the range.  He then asked how many rounds I had shot.  I explained that I had taken a course with my local police department and had spent time shooting a 9mm, a .40 caliber and my .38 special.  I told him maybe 100 rounds to which he said his requirement was 150 rounds.  He told me to bring an experienced person back with me before I could use the range. Needless to say he will never see me again and I will gladly warn all women to not even bother wasting their time.

name: Tom Green
text: For those all complaining about asking about experience, I glad he does. I once saw 2 females next to me at another gun range in Florida who damn near shot the person next to them when one pulled the trigger , got scared and pointed the gun at the guy next to them for him to take the snub nose while her damn finger still on the trigger. Thank-you robert for telling those people to   get trained first and come back. I feel personally safer......

name: Tom Green
text: For those all complaining about asking about experience, I glad he does. I once saw 2 females next to me at another gun range in Florida who damn near shot the person next to them when one pulled the trigger , got scared and pointed the gun at the guy next to them for him to take the snub nose while her damn finger still on the trigger. Thank-you robert for telling those people to   get trained first and come back. I feel personally safer......

name: Josh Garland
text:
If you do not want someone being blunt and forward with you then do not go to this store. If you want someone to be honest and straight then this is the store for you. I went in on a random idea after eating dinner. I have never been inside the rack but when I did I walked out the door with a Colt Python!

The store isn't flashy but I am completely satisfied with the out come. I plan to take my wife back to shoot on the range.

name: Douglas Kaul
text: Recently took a gun that needed repair to Robert.  He quickly figured out what was wrong, ordered some parts and fixed it. It works perfectly.  Nice job Robert!

name: Nick Rambo
text: Safety is his #1 priority. Good hand gun range. There's about 5-6 booths to shoot from with sliding targets. $1/target $15 range fee. Military gets a discount.

name: Jacob Mowry
text: I've been going up here for about 2 yrs now. Robert and his staff is very knowledgeable and friendly. I would definitely recommend to anyone in the area to check them out.

name: Richard Deloach
text: Pretty good service, also has indoor gun range which is nice living in the city. Pistols on though. But never the less good place.

name: Jason Nicholson
text: Robert's priorities are everyone's safety, and good service. Not only does he have convenient hours, but he always has ammo to shoot (even if the quantities are currently limited). Great time and will be back.

name: Anonymous
text: Don’t go in, get put on the spot by an overly dramatic guy by holding his little plastic gun with your thumb in the back. Because “you will come out of the shooting range bloody and crying, injured” and he will request someone who has “shot 100’s of thousands of rounds from a pistol” to accompany you before you can shoot there. Wow. Be sure to go in on your toes, Definitely an overly tense environment. What a shame.

name: Carl Voth
text: It is always a pleasure going to Roberts Gun Rack, He always make you feel welcome.

name: Wendell Bomar
text: Although the owner is big on gun safety (as he should be) the one thing i noticed was the lack of a range safety officer.  People were in the range room that were not shooting at that time loading and handling the firearms behind the shooters. Kind of wants to make you keep your head on a swivel. Got sprayed with scrapnel from bullets hitting the metal target hanger that were just a few feet out from the shooters to our left. Was a little apprehensive after a couple of those so we decided to leave after that. That was our first time at this range and safe to say it will be out only time.

name: ChadW
text: One of the cheapest places to shoot, usually can get in the range quickly, have always had a good experience on every occasion I have been.

name: dwashbu1
text: Love this place!! Super helpful and nice. Great prices.

name: alome chanthasinh
text: Great place, great man to deal with. Straight to the point, no BS...go check him out. 👍👍

name: Phillip Harding
text: Roberts offers fair prices for the current situation, the ability to custom order a wide variety if products, and best of all, the only indoor shooting range in town. Some may shy away from the look of the place, but i have frequented this shop for the last 2 years, and due to a strict tolerance for safety, i have not seen any unsafe behavior on the range, and that's comforting to know when sharing a range with complete strangers.

name: Gordon Seybert
text: So frustrating. I've been shooting for 20 years, never been told I am irresponsible. I am very serious about safety.   No previous "official" training = turned away. I really hate this guy... Wouldn't buy a cotton patch from him.

name: Sherrinekia Norwood
text: Was not allowed access due to my lack of shooting experience. I was with my husband who did have experience, was still denied access. I feel like I was discriminated against, and I will not be returning.

name: J.P. Clowes
text: Great experience. I took my son shooting for the very first time. They gave a very thorough safety briefing that really took hold, and he did well.

name: Tim Jones
text: Robert's Gun Rack is a great place to shoot. Robert is very knowledgeable and is a STARIGHT-SHOOTER! CLEAN, SAFE, and AFFORDABLE!!!

name: Todd Mcnorton
text: The knowledge and experience of the owner and attention  to safety was outstanding. I will  definitely be  back.

name: tiana kimber
text: Was denied access to the range even though I am an experienced shooter while with my brother, who is a Marine. He was told he wasn't experienced enough, "no offense".

name: Lee Lane
text: Very safety oriented. I'very brought 3 new shooters there over the years and Robert personally checks to make sure they know range safety and etiquette.

name: John Paul
text: I've read alot of these reviews... was worried on how I was going to be treated. But this was my first time here.. and the gentleman Robert (owner) was very pleasant in my visit. I give this 5 stars because the location is great, the booths are very good each one has a fan that is your own to use. Your going to a shooting range.... so you should have commen sence on how to handle a firearm. I will be coming here to test my firearms from now on. Very good Robert I do appreciate your establishment and your commitment  to safety. Looking forward to come another day.

name: Frances Mendez
text: Robert is a knowledgeable guy. His primary concern is gun safety. The people that have a problem with....well, I don't want them shooting next to me!!!

name: Matt Campbell
text:
First, go to SELF DEFENSE READINESS TRAINING on Bruns Drive and pay the extra $ . Its a nicer establishment and there isnt Robert.  You will have to pass the interview but its not biased.

Second, know how to pass the "hold my fake gun" test. I wasnt thinking right and wrapped my thumbs around the back of the fake gun.. hopped in my car and was like, now why the hell did I do that and normally dont .. oh well. Waste of time. Thats why I read reviews. Hes not a racist or a jerk, just a trickster. Not everyone has somebody they can come back with like Robert recommended.  Robert instead of saying "youre disqualified" why dont you hop up and educate .

name: J. Lynn
text: Edit- Just to clear this up a little in case it wasn't Robert I spoke with. I don't know the guys name I was talking to but I was in the store less than 30 minutes and got charged over $55 for shooting the guns he "insisted" we try out. I was ready to buy a pistol for my wife but I got tired of hearing this guy talk about himself and talk to me like a child. I bought the pistol we decided on elsewhere $40 cheaper. Whoever he was, he was rude and and full of himself. I understand a business has to make money and it was my fault for not clearing it up before going back to the range, but that is not how you treat a customer if you wanna keep them a customer. I stand behind my rating of two stars because I definitely, "Disliked it." If it wasn't Robert I was speaking with I suggest he select better employees.

name: Graham Forsythe
text: I went in to order a $1,600 rifle.  While I was in there, I saw another rifle in the rack I probably would have bought out of hand.  There were two guys behind the counter, one having a conversation with a 16-year old and the other just watching.  I kept waiting for one of them to at least acknowledge me and say "I'll be with you in a minute".  After 10 minutes of being ignored, I finally walked out.  I bought the rifle at another gun shop for $60 more, but I'll gladly pay more for service.  I have two other guns I'm thinking about getting in the next year or so.  These guys didn't lose a sale, they lost a customer.

name: Robert Harrison
text: Had a great time with my daughter there today.  Very friendly, knowledgable and helpful.  Highly recommend to everyone in the Mobile area.

name: Aaron
text: Went there to teach my wife to shoot. Robert asked me questions based on mine and hers experience with pistols since I was to teach her. He allowed me to do after showing her a few more things and making sure that she fully understood everything. Even tho it took us a while to get started I'm very happy he did this to make sure that our and everyone elses safety was put first. What he was trying to get her to do today was get her over the anxsity. After 20 min of pumping herself up she finnaly did it. We both had fun and will definitely return in the near future.

name: Timothy Byrd
text: I have known robert for quite sometime now and have learned this... If you have a problem with him then you have a problem with yourself. Robert is very aggressive on safety and making sure you know what you are doing before you take a LOADED HAND GUN ON A RANGE WITH OTHER PEOPLE. Me being a Law Enforcement officer, I have seen other officers who can barely make the cut on the range, so officer or not, dont get your panties in a wad when he comes at you with his saftey spill. As for the retards that have given him bad reviews, like I said before, you have a problem with yourself. I read one that said he is a know it all. Well if you were there asking questions, then you must not know to much. If you do know that much, Why were you in there asking questions? Get over yourself. To the guy who said he has the only gun range around mobile so he thinks he can charge what he wants.... You sir are an idiot. There are a total of 4 gun ranges in mobile. Do some research before you pop off at the mouth degrading the way some one runs there business. The other gun ranges in mobile all charge the same amount to shoot. You too can get over yourself. I have done business with robert and many other gun stores in mobile. I prefer going to robert because he takes care of me. I may not agree with some of the things he does or the way he does things but in the end, I got what I came for and got it at a good price with friendly service. If you want to go somewhere that they kiss your a$$ and tell you what you want to hear, dont go to Roberts. If you want to go somewhere that will be blount, give you an honest OPINION, and invite you back to talk guns and gear... Check him out.

text: Place was very safety oriented.  Good shooting area

name: Tiffany Roberts
text: I drove over an hour to come shoot. I was immediately interrogated with questions like "Have you ever taken a course?," "How many rounds have you shot through the pistol you brought?" etc. etc. I have a lot of shooting experience but at the time had not taken an official course. He told me some random story about a woman blowing her thumb off. Then he told me to leave and "come back with my dad." I am a grown woman, and my dad lives 200 miles away. There wasn't a single other person in there. Even if I wasn't very experienced, he could've taken the time to teach me, but I guess he was just too lazy or too sexist.

The guys working were super friendly and provided great customer service.  Ffl transfers are available here as well.  A great local business providing service to the people of Shelby County and all of Alabama.  Give these a guys a look for your next firearm related purchase, you won’t be disappointed.

name: Tyler Richards
text:
Don't let the size of the store fool you, their selection of firearms is exceptional. Being in law enforcement, I have had many gun purchasing experiences and consider Alabama Guns and Outdoors one of my best yet.

For first time gun owners looking for a comfortable buying experience, look no further. You don't find gun businesses with an atmosphere and owner like this often.

name: PressStart ToRetry
text: Very nice guys and willing to help with whatever you need. Stopped in just to look around and enjoyed the conversation while I was there. Made a small purchase and the owner gave me a discount. I will definitely shop here again.

name: Gerardo Hernandez
text: This gun shop is arguably one of the best in Birmingham even though it may not be the largest. The staff has and continues to be very respectful and insightful to all patrons and I personally have a very positive experience every time I go. The selection of firearms is great and good quality; although it may not have the largest they do carry worthwhile guns and equipment worth buying. It is an overall great place for first-time gun-buyers as well as the experienced.

name: Alexandra Gomez
text: I am so happy I was able to buy my first gun from Alabama Guns & Outdoors. Everyone was very helpful and nice. They took their time to show me guns and helped me choose the perfect one for me. Russell even took the time to show me how to break down my gun and put it back together. If you're in need of buying a gun, you should definitely go see them. Thank y'all so much!

text: Cool place to visit. My 1st time at a Bass Pro Shop. Would recommend going at least once to check out the set up,the Bass and Alligator Gar tank&the gorgeous boats are a plus!! Lots of Country Instagram worthy props in there! Lol 😆😆😆 Also I thought most of the stuff was over priced in there. Just a little!

name: Mudd Mannipulater
text:
Smaller store than what I am use to. Staff was around but not overly helpful. The woman working the door was very helpful and a great example of how All the employees should act. The check out process was excellent. The staff on the 2nd floor were on their phones and they showed no motivation. The guy in the gun department was the same. He could not find the item I wanted. He didn't offer to order it in or to order it on-line. I was willing to do either.
The boat and ATV guy lost a sale  since they could not break free from their conversation to help me. I hate pushy sales people but at least acknowledge me after you see me taking pictures and returning to the same area 3 times.
I never saw anyone in the clothing departments so I didn't get the items that I wanted  to stock up on.
I return to Bass Pro because of the quality of the products and it is normally easy to get help. I did not find that at this store.
It was a surprise to find the outside water features seemed neglected too.  I  didn't see any fish and the fountains and falls that are normally seen were not there either.
Luckily I can find another store close by to get what I'm looking for.
I spent FAR less than I normally do at THIS Bass Pro store and I still need to do my spring shopping.
I will not return to this store if I can another one close by.

Please understand that this store is not exactly bad, it just doesn't have the warm welcoming flow and energy that I have grown fond to.

name: Vance Blackburn
text:
This place is enormous!  We have visited one of their similar stores in Pennsylvania and were not disappointed.

Incredible detail to store layout and decorating makes this a place to see for yourself. A true place to bring the whole family for hours of enjoyment.

The kids will enjoy everything from the untold number of mounted animals to the shooting gallery. The usual point of sale goodies can be found at every register, but the real goodies are found in the old time store... The fudge is awesome!  Sit down meals and available at the in-store restaurant offering a variety of animal meats.

I was impressed with the knowledge the staff had in their respective departments. The gun area had well trained staff and offered many hints on the model I was interested in.  My wife hit the women's clothing like a fire sale and found some great outfits.

This store is very accessable to those people with disabilities. The elevators are great for those of us with bad knees.

This place gets a big five star rating.

name: Kim Low

name: Mike Brown
text:
I shopped online for sale items and placed order. All went well with online purchases and received email a few minutes later that my order was in progress and I would receive a email when all the order was ready for pickup. All this was at 6:00 am. I thought all was good and I wasn't going to have to stand in line at the store because I'm not in physical condition for that and do most of my shopping online. Thirteen hours later I received a email from Bass Pro that my order was canceled due to items now was not available and wouldn't be offered at that price again after that sale date.
The online service is not your friend and is not a good way to shop deals at Bass Pro..☹
There's other stores that have excellent online service !

Only one of the paper towel dispensers were working, and barely at that, only if you pulled it out in a certain way. It took 3 strangers and myself to find the working dispenser and get paper towels out of it, it was a team effort.
There were far less people in the store than previous years, so I'm not sure what their excuse would be. Most of the children's attractions were broken or half working as well. The kids were practically bored to tears. We only stayed for pictures with Santa. Our wait was 2 hours. And by all means it should have been half that time. There really weren't many people in the store. Crafts that were supposed to start at noon didn't begin till around 12:30 and the craft person was stale and thoroughly uninterested in their job. Before when we had come there was quite a bit of interaction and Mrs. Clause even came over to help.
It was a total waste of time coming out here. Their restaurant isn't even open anymore. So much for being a kids event. I didn't even make our purchases, and we obviously had lunch elsewhere. I can buy this stuff elsewhere too lol.

name: Michael Thomas
text:
Mr Jim Hagale / CEO Johnny Morris

I purchased a boat through your company (Spanish Fort) and wanted to directly share my TERRIBLE experience with you.

13 Jul 20:  Purchased the Regency R230LE3 Sport for $67,759

After the staff inspection and detail of the boat, it was delivered to my home on 13 Jul.

After delivery I called sales rep to inform him that: Boat Cover not included, Ski Pole missing, cushion springs to get into the departments not working, missing console cover piece, crack in fiberglass of console, latch for shower bracket broken, trickle charger outlet not secured to boat. (Items needing replacement when purchased: Co Captain Chair had tear, 2 seat cushions had tears, sun shade cover needed replacement, radio (2 control panels) need replacement).

14 Jul 20:  Put boat in the water, trim gauge did not work..... AND BOAT STARTED TO SINK ON RIGHT SIDE!

Got boat out of the water, called sales rep and I took the boat back to Spanish Ft on 15 July.

Determined, leak in right side pontoon. Was informed I must go through the warranty process to get it fixed.  I have played this game now for 8 days.  NO CHANGE TO THE BOAT!  STILL WAITING FOR WARRANTY OFFICE TO CONTACT DEALERSHIP!

I told them to replace the boat or take the boat back.

I have been told by your Finance Dept to call dealership.

I have been told by your Corp Customer Service Rep to call dealership.

Dealership says:  That's not how it works, you will not get a replacement and we will not cancel the loan.

So, here we are.  Me emailing the CEO to get help!

The boat has not even been titled or funded yet.  This experience and your company customer service is absolutely unacceptable.  Bass Pro Shop sells a retired military man a boat that starts to sink in the first 30 mins of ever touching the water, confirmed by staff it has a leak and was told.... we will file a warranty claim.  Sorry about your Luck!

Can't wait to share this experience with my community, with your community!

Mike Thomas

name: Ronald Clement
text: Extremely disappointed at the customer service I received at this store location. I tried to purchase a flannel/hoodie combo shirt, that was marked on one of the middle store isle racks, for $17.99 as advertised on the sign above the rack ( at 0910 AM). They were marked down from $44.99. I went and did about 15 more minutes of shopping and went to check out (at 0925 AM). At check out the item showed up as $44.99 and I said I would take it over to refund for them to research the price further. The associate at the refund desk stated the price was never $17.99 and there was no sign there showing it was ever that price. My wife walked back there and could you imaging the signs mysteriously vanished from the time I picked up the item at the rack to the time I went to check out. I was made to look like a liar and a cheat by the refund associate and Bass Pro. The only thing they had to say was they had mistakenly left the sales signs up from the weekend and I would have been okay with that. Instead I had to listen to the other refund associate say I was in the right and the signs were removed late but she could not make the other associate listen to her. Funny how they want to thank you for your military service one minute and then make you out to be a liar in front of other customers the next. I will no longer be shopping at the Bass Pro Spanish Fort location and I would suggest that all customers take photos of sales prices on the racks for they are to be susceptible removed at a moments notice to prove the customer is wrong and vendor is in the right.

name: Benjamin Harms
text: I'm not a sports lover or fisherman by any stretch of the imagination. But, I found this store to be really incredible!  The layout was a little overwhelming and felt sprawling. The line to see Santa was unbelievably long, so we took a pass on that. According to my sister, the best time to go for a picture with Santa is on a weeknight, rather than on a Sunday afternoon. Haha The stairway that trails up beside the fish tank was in and of itself a fun attraction. The elevators were even nicely themed to compliment everything. I was really impressed with the entire ecosystem that they have designed. The prices were higher than I would ever want to pay for simple gift ideas, but this just isn't a simple gift kind of place. The gift shop had some yummy options from party mix to crazy flavors of mixed nuts and cotton candy, and even Bacon Hot Chocolate (but even at only $1.49 per pack, I was still afraid to buy and try it). We also ate at the restaurant, which I wrote a review for separately. Great experiences to be had here!

text: Every year I bring my family to bass pro shop to take pictures with santa do some Christmas shopping. I love bass pro shop all together but today we had a horrible experience. We had to digitally sign up to take pictures with santa and we got there at 11:30 the wait was 2.5 hrs so after shopping going out to eat we came back at 2 exactly 2.5 hrs to find out there was another 50 minutes to wait okay no big deal we do more shopping with three kids finally we get the message at 3:30 that its time to take pictures with Santa to only find out their system is down and it'll be another two hours of waiting and all the people who weren't able to sign up to take pictures will be completely turned away as the bass pro shop employee stated. My kids were crushed when we told them we had to leave because I had to go to work in an hour and they spent all day being patient waiting to see santa. I'm one family out of a whole store full that went through this I hope they come up with a better system by next year but honestly I dont think we will be coming back to see santa it's much easier and less of a hassle to just go to the mall.

name: Stephen Hoist
text: I have been going to the Spanish Fort location for several years.  It had been a while since I was last in there.  I have never had an issue before but this time I was there to spend some money.  I went up to look at a  rifle scope that I had been looking at online.  I went upstairs and took the long way to get there.  We were greeted properly walking in so didn't see any reason to think anything else.  We walked through the bows, then walked past the rifle racks to the scopes.  The guys working the counter were working with other customers so I looked around, I found the one I wanted to see.  In that process, I found another that I was interested in I looked up to see the status of the salespeople and they were over on the other side talking to each other and what looked to be looking at a phone behind the counter.  I left the counter went to check on kids who were by the aquarium.  We walked around and I decided I was going to get both of the scopes I found.  I went back and both salespeople were talking to one person.  So while I was waiting, I found a third scope I wanted.  The lady they were talking to left and they went back to the other end of the counter and did what they were doing before.  Now I don't like when a salesperson hovers over me, but I have worked in retail enough to at least let a customer know I am there to help.  I couldn't even get that out of them, so we walked away.  They missed a out a $4K sale.  I am not going to beg for them to help me.  They weren't busy.  The way I see it is they were just busy ignoring me.  Walking to the exit, I found a gear bag for a decent price and decided to buy it.  The man at the cash register was awesome.  If the guys at the gun counter were, Bass Pro would have sold me a lot more than a $12.99 bag.  I will go back again.  Like I said, this was the first time I had a bad experience there.

text: Brought in a 13 Concept A3 baitcaster which is a 200 dollar and up reel. I have taken many of reels to this location and have never had an issue at all with any of them untillll today. I confidently walked around and did some more shopping picked up my reel and checked out and went on about my work day. On my way home I peeked In the box to find the top of my new expensive reel scratched up and the coating removed. I have no confidence in this store was told that they would handle the situation and call me back later and low and behold here we are with a scratched up reel I do not want to fish with due to it might corroding and the warranty is void. I'm going here today with my 4 year old because i have a bunch of gift cards saved up and can get him some cool toys. I'm sure they have some specialty stuff that's hard to come by at other places and the staff always seems helpful unless it's a mad house day in which case I just wait my turn someone will help you when they can.

text: My husband went to the Bass Pro Shop in Daphne, Al. today, looking to purchase a small boat or kayak for fishing. He went into the tracker boat section, spoke with two elderly gentlemen, he doesnt rememeber his name but the gentleman that let him back in the building after looking at the boats outside didnt say anything to him, just opened the door and walked away. So he approached another gentleman sitting at the desk, asked about one of the boats they had outside and about financing, the gentleman’s response was if you dont have a 700 or better they wont finance you and they wont finance anything under $5000.00. Assuming because of how my husband looked that his score was under a 700. So my husband went inside and started looking at kayaks, he was up there for close to an hour and was not approached one time by a sales associate to see if he needed help, at that point he left the store. So not only did you lose a possible sale on a boat you also lost out on the sale of a kayak. Your salesman in the tracker boat section are extremely rude and all your employees need some educating on customer service and he will never shop in another Bass Pro Shop again.

It's also a full service screen print shop and they also can make your school logo's!!   I will be recommending this great storet to everyone I know!!! And me and Jacob can't wait to go back again and again!🏈🏀⚾⚽🏅🎾🏉😀

name: Andrew Farrow
text: I stopped by on a trip to Sipsey fork. They have an amazing selection of flies and other items you may need for a trip. The guys here are extremely knowledgeable and are happy to chat with you for a while and give you some good recommendations for what you may need for any fishing trip. They also know and provide the dam schedule which was fantastic for planning a trip since you don't want to drive all the way out here just to find out you won't be able to fish cause the dam is generating.

name: Clay Gary
text: Had a great time. Guides were super nice. Highly recommend.

name: Rick Mason
text: Had a great time with Brandon our guide!  He knows where to find big Rainbow Trout!

name: Bryan Jenkins
text: Had an awesome morning being guided by MC. She did a wonderful job of teaching us the basics and it was my son’s first time. Needless to say he is now “hooked”.

name: Keith Crouch
text:
Great experience with Brandon as our guide.  My Father-in-law and myself are rookies in the fly fishing world.  Brandon is a great teacher and is very patient!  I will definitely be back and encourage anyone that loves to fish to give these guys a try and definately check them shop out!
Keith Crouch

name: James Huff
text:
We had a great time discovering and catching Rainbow trout for the first time!  The guided instruction was useful and memorable for future  use.......we intend to fish more.  All services were as advertised.  I am definitely planning to return with all the guys.

I would go to the fly shop first before going to the water.  I am glad that we got some instruction first before going on our first Rainbow trout trip!

name: Jason Cheney
text:
Extremely friendly and knowledgeable family.
They absolutely love to talk fishing.
Bought waders and boots for my wife and they took all the time she needed to make the right choice for her.

While my wife was trying on the waders & boots I learned a few things I was doing wrong chasing stripers on the lake from Mary Carole. Who incidentally just finished a guide trip with a client that landed a 20" rainbow!

Brandon and Mary run a great shop. Plenty of fishing gear and tying supplies.
They're quite a ways from our place in arley but I, and now my wife, really enjoy getting down there when we can.

Highly recommended whether you're a complete newbie or a seasoned veteran.

name: Tyler Hunter
text: Outstanding fly shop. They are very willing to teach or help you with anything related to becoming a better angler. I learned a lot of good stuff from Randy and Brandon.

name: Joseph Wolf
text: Quality service and instruction

name: Anthony Josey
text: Outstanding customer service, went above and beyond to make sure I found what I needed.

name: Carl Cathey
text: I stopped by outside of their normal business hours, and they were very accommodating.  Great folks, I'll go back for sure!

name: Connor Baker
text: Love this place! If you want to learn about Smith Lake or Sipsey Fork, book a guide trip with Brandon, he knows what he is talking about and it is a blast! I also have purchased two rods here.  Randy was very helpful and helped me find the right rod for what I wanted to fish! Can't recommend enough! Great shop and great people!

name: Leah Rasbury
text: We did the 11 mile trip yesterday and it was really nice! The staff was very friendly and knowledgeable and the shop itself is so awesome! Definitely a highlight, was playing Bama Cab in the van on the ride back to the shop after our trip!!! I would definitely recommend this place to my friends and family!

name: Shawn Stevens
text: Great service and advice on fishing and supplies needed. Super friendly staff! Will definitely come back for a guided fishing trip!

name: Taylor Hall
text:
Cannot recommend this place enough! Booked a half-day wading trip to start learning how to fly fish and it was even better than I had hoped for!

Brandon is a fantastic guide who was incredibly patient and broke everything down in a very straight forward manner, making it easy to make decent casts and start working to get better. He took the time to teach us stuff so that we could come back and fish on our own.

You can tell he his guide service is VERY kid friendly!

I cannot wait to work on the stuff he taught us and take another trip to get additional instruction!

****edited: I was able to work my way back on my own to fish the same river and caught two beautiful rainbows on my own! Second trip fly fishing and I have to give credit to the guiding service because without the initial lesson I wouldn’t have figured it out so quick!!!

name: Jacob Maples
text: Great selection on everything from flies, rods, reeds, and outerwear. Awesome people who know the water and are more then willing to help.

name: Pat combs
text: Wonderful, owner helped us out a lot on Places to go.Hot slots!!

text: L@@@@llaall//well stocked, professional,  and helpful

name: Brandon White
text: Great people! I’ve made the drive from Birmingham multiple times to shop here. Most memorable was buying my first fly outfit and getting some great casting instruction. Highly recommended.

name: David Davis
text: Great folks!!!! Hospitable and friendly!!! Thanks as always!

name: Bo Turner
text: I want to give a big shout out to the guys at Riverside Fly Shop.  Yesterday I went out with the owner Brandon Jackson for a little private instruction and my first try at fly fishing.  These guys are incredibly helpful and patient with a clumsy beginner like me.  If you’re a fisherman and want to try something different or if you are a beginner and just want to give it a try I recommend these guys highly.  This would also be an awesome Christmas gift for an outdoorsy person.  It’s also worth the drive to stop by and take a look around their shop or ask questions.  Thanks Randy and Brandon for all the help!  I had a blast.

name: Vicki Raynes
text: Our vacation here was wonderful. We camped here and the site was very secluded. The owner of the shop was very informative about the best places on the Sipsy River to fly fish and what flies to use.  The view was wonderful and the River was beautiful. A great place to have a very private vacation.

name: Jon Nash
text: My wife surprised me with a guided trip on Fathers Day, and I learned more in that 4 hours than all of my previous fly fishing trips combined. Excellent, personalized, and patient instruction, and super fun. Brandon is the Bill Nye the science guy of guides, with the temperament of a monk. I had the time of my life. I left with a wealth of knowledge and stocked up on quality equipment at Riverside before heading home to Birmingham.

text: I was hesitant at first to place an order with this company due to the nature of some of the reviews. name: JS
text:
Gouging with over pricing of Rifle Primers.  Jacked up the price 7 times the normal selling price.  No Thanks LG Outdoors!

Update: Received a response from LG Outdoors and they pretty much played the blame game on bots buying up all the Primers. At $419.99 for a box of 1000 Primers is a ridiculous price. Normally primers are $0.04 each and with this price, it makes it $0.41 each. Just shows human greed from a company. Understand there is a shortage. Maybe hold off on selling Primers until supplies come readily available and go back to a reasonable price. I yes I have not bought from this company and never will. Karma will come back to you in the end.

name: Adam Osiecki
text:
Price gouging at its finest. I received a notification that they had primers in stock, so I went to place an order. They were asking $315/1000 for Federal small pistol match primers and $250 for Federal large rifle primers. These normally go for about $50 and $40 respectively. They are 100% trying to take advantage of people due to the shortage. Between this and the fact that they are probably one of the worst reviewed companies I've ever seen I can't believe anybody gives this place a dime. It'd probably be less painful to burn the money you were going to give them and throw yourself down the stairs.

Edited to add:  Your response is laughable. All the reputable stores (Midway USA, Natchez, Brownells, Cabelas, etc.) are still selling primers for regular price. They just sell out as soon as they get them in stock so you need to have in stock alerts set up and be ready to buy immediately. You look even worse for trying to justify being a price gouger.

Edited to add again:  I see you've changed your response from justifying your price gouging to now claiming there is some coordinated effort to attack your company.  I personally don't know, nor have I communicated in any way with any of the other reviewers.  If you think reviews from perspective buyers who opted not to buy from your company due to shady business practices are irrelevant, then you are a complete moron.  But go ahead and try to dismiss valid reviews of your company genius.

resp.text: We are truly as upset about the price of primers as the public , but we have no controls over that.  You and the public set the price.  If these primers were any lower cost, you would not be able to buy them because some else would have already bought all of them.  The only reason you have any chance at all buy some is due to the fact they are priced at the low end of the market price, any lowered and they sell out instantly before you even get a chance.  So is it better not to be able to buy any at all, or is it better to be able to pay a little more and just buy enough for you immediate needs.  The public sets the price they are willing to pay.  When the goods are priced lower than market, they are gone instantly ad most people never have the chance to buy any at all.  More often than most people realize the market price for some things is far below cost and dealer and distributors end up selling them at a loss.  The good must continue to move, it does no good to eave product on the shelve that doesn't, it gets discounted until it reaches the market price and ten it will finally sell and if that is below cost we have to eat it.  You never hear customers complain that they bought some thing too cheap.  It works both ways my friend.  Personally I will not pay the going prices and I thing every one needs to slow down so prices go back down to normal.
