name: Southern Adventure Outdoors
text: My name is Brandon Conley. I too had a poor experience with Shelly. I ordered an item from Amazon. an air purifier. It was sent "adult signature required" in error by the warehouse. That is different than "signature required" shipping. Adult sig required  means no changes, no address change, no local UPS store pickup. LG outdoors tried to change it on Thursday. I tried to have it re-routed and couldnt. Saturday delivery was not even an option. I had no way to sign for the package without taking time off work. I could only pick up from a UPS hub that was over an hour from my house so I had UPS return the item. The item arrived back to them on Friday. On Tuesday I told them to just send the item back via regular shipping. A man from customer service and I had a pleasant conversation about this on Thursday. This week Shelly has been in. On Tuesday she said she was waiting on the warehouse to respond to their emails. Today which is Wednesday I sent another email asking for an update since I was suppose to hear back by end of business on Tuesday. Shelly told me they were still waiting on the warehouse and I should hear back by the end of the day today. I told her that is exactly what you told me yesterday. She then said they were waiting to hear back from me on if I wanted a refund or return shipment. I told her that we had emailed yesterday about just sending it back and that everything she has told me so far has been a lie and all seems repetitive. Shelly then raised her voice, changed her tone to a very condescending one. After you all made an error and I still was patient and tried to work you, you give me the customer and attitude and hang up the phone? So yes. #$%* you just give me a refund. I even called back to give her another chance. She answered the phone with an attitude. Look at their feedback on amazon and on here. It seems Shelly has been losing more business than her services are worth.  Their negative reviews are increasing according to their amazon profile. 20% over the past year and now 28% over the past 6 months with less reviews being left. My advice is to close the doors on Shelly or close the doors on your 20 year old business. I will work with you to correct an error and we tried that until she got involved. I understand that mistakes happen but I will not be downgraded and spoken to like a child while attempting to do business with you.

name: D O
text:
Terrible experience and I sure wish I would have read these reviews prior to purchasing!  Although the gun came quickly and sales staff is friendly the owner himself seems a bit off balance.  I am active duty military stationed in AL and when I went to pick up the rifle I showed my military ID and my AL concealed carry permit.  The owner wanted a copy of my USMC orders bringing me here to AL and when I stated that is not something we generally carry on our persons, he stated it was federal law. When I questioned him in an attempt to get a better understanding of the law and using as example in the last 18 months I have purchased weapons from Walter Craig, Gulf States Distributors, and Gander Mountain in Montgomery with no requirement to furnish a copy of my military orders, he no kidding exploded!  Literally told me to get the (f-bleep) out of his store and he would charge me for a restocking fee!  This was one of the most insane and oddest moments I have ever had in a retailers shop.  This experience is difficult to describe in believable terms and was rather off putting.  As far as I could tell he was the only angry person on the premises.

I was able to talk to his sales staff and they explained that it was his policy.  I understand that and the information upfront would have been extremely helpful.  I want to comply with any reasonable store policies and would have had I known this was an issue for the owner.  In the end my wife was able to email me a copy and I completed the transaction.  His salesman saved the purchase and I truly believe he is a sincere and helpful person.

Having said all that I really think purchasing from this establishment is a mistake and I wish I would have walked after the verbal assault and string of profanities.  If you do decide to venture into his place of business be careful; He appeared genuinely angry (which should concern any responsible gun owner), completely narcissistic, not open to any conversation that would question his authority, and is armed!  This man went from 0 to 100 in a nano-second over an issue that I still can’t quite figure out.  Could be he is not a fan of the Marine Corps or the military in general...hope that is not the case and he was just having a bad day but I won’t trust him with my business again.

name: joey walker
text:
For the managers of this store.... please tell me what quota you must meet before you get to go home? What legally set hours must you follow to achieve said quota? When you are holding up a delivery driver for 30+ minutes BEFORE even answering the door.... you loose us money, make it nearly impossible to get home, and push back all further deliveries.

A driver unlike a store employee (store employee has set hours by their employer) a driver has legal hours we must follow for the safe operation of the vehicles we drive. Our employer makes a set quota of loads/ stops before we can park for the night and go home. Anything that goes wrong with that quota drops everything about that day!

Think of that next time you decide to leave a driver at the back door unanswered!!!

text: Management at this location unfortunately provided the worst customer service I’ve ever experienced. When attempting to remedy a faulty gift card, they made it very clear that they preferred not to help and that they had “other things to do.” They yelled at both me (in public) and the customer service representative from Walmart’s gift card vendor who was attempting to help local management issue a new card (after local management suggested that I remedy the situation by calling the number on the back of the card, again). The representative on the phone couldn’t believe we were being treated in such a manner. I spent an hour and a half patiently trying to get help while two managers continuously walked away in the middle of a conversation, after turning around and forcing me to talk to their backs, while the third said she was going home and was no longer interested in helping. One also referred to me as “this” to another employee before storming off. I might have understood management’s disrespectfulness and laziness if I had been unpleasant but that certainly wasn’t the case. I highly recommend visiting another location, or another store altogether, if kind customer service is needed.

name: nsanejain
text: First of all, I am disabled and no one would want to live in my body even for an hour. When I arrived, fresh from having an MRI which made me hurt even worse from laying flat, I saw a ride along cart and got on it. I was having a very hard time walking. The cart was over half charged but the only one on that side. (Of course plenty were left out in the parking lot, guess I should have gotten one of those.) Anyway, as I'm starting to go, a greeter tells me, ma'am, that was is being charged, and needs to continue charging. Made me feel like I couldn't use it. So I took it back, and hobbled to shop best I could. I couldn't get everything I needed, because the pain was excruciating. She did not offer to find me one, either. The more I hobbled around, the more it irritated me. I should have gotten her name and contacted corporate. I know who to contact as I used to work for Wal-Mart before I became fully disabled. I am so disabled, I had a "tough judge" and they concluded that I couldn't work ANY job. But this lady made me feel as if I couldn't use the cart which was well over half charged. I know she was a medium complicated, a bit heavy set and wore glasses. I will still contact corporate over this. I had a helper with me, but couldn't stay in the store long enough to finish shopping. My helper had to just take my groceries to checkout for me as I hobbled back to my handicapped parking spot to wait in the passenger side. It's already bad enough that the store was out of a lot of stuff, but the thing I am really upset about was being treated like I didn't need the cart. Next time I will be quite rude instead of my usual nice personality. That lady should be put in the backroom on cap 2 where she belongs. A greeter, who is part of AP, should be very nice and accommodating. When I worked at Wal-Mart I always went above and beyond for customers. Customers are who buys the things that pay employees. If I didn't live 40 minutes away from a Wal-Mart I would go back and get her name. I do plan to, but will go ahead tomorrow and contact corporate. I will not go back to whittlesey rd Wal-Mart ever again, except to get her name. None of my family, nor myself will ever shop there again. Do better, and don't treat people less than, it will only lead to write ups and dismissal. Very dissappointed and hurt honestly. Wish that lady had to live in my body for a whole week. She would be crying in pain every day and see why she should treat people better. And anyone reading this, when you are treated badly at any Wal-Mart, go and complain to CORPORATE. The managers may not do anything, but corporate takes things like this seriously. And know that the Wal-Mart employees make at least $13 an hour now. They should be doing MUCH better. Blessings to the good people still out there.

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️💫  For Renea that took my call Today 12-9-20 at 12:50pm at  Walmart on Whittlesey  Blvd, Columbus, Ga 31909. I needed blood work done at Quest Diagnostic. I accidentally left my drivers license inside Quest and did not notice until a little over an hour and 40 miles later and 10 minutes before Quest closed for lunch and I was Frantic 🤯 wanting to be sure that they were there and I didn’t drop them somewhere unfortunately the only number I could find was automated only I was really starting to Panic my husband told me to call the Walmart I’m thinking it’s the Christmas season the store was packed and I don’t believe Quest is an actual part of Walmart but with time ticking and me panicking (I am from NYC with a NYC drivers license that cost about $100 to replace and a flight back to NYC in a few days) on the verge of crying  there was a voice of an Angel on the other end she said” Hello Thank You for Calling Walmart this Renea How may i help you?” I explained to Renea my situation and before I could finish she ask if I would hold on that she would go right away before they closed for lunch  and she returned with the amazing news that she had my licenses Renea went above and beyond for me If everyone working in customer service was like Renea it would be an amazing, and all would be right in my world ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
.

text: They enforce masks to be worn when shopping but 50 to 70 percent of all employees working not at cash registers that i saw were wearing the mask around their throat. The point of the mask is so that when you are near other people, you don't catch germs transmitted by them. Pulling your masks down totally defeats that. The last bit of offenders I saw covered the mouths but not the nose of the employees. Again, defeats the purpose. I would have to say out of all the employees I saw working, only 5 of them wore the masks the right way the entire time. And we wonder why Columbus has one of the highest amounts of Covid cases per capita.

text: Ahhhh Wal Mart-what can I say that hasn’t already been said? The store (at least late at night) is a mess, the restrooms are a mess, it looks as though the grocery and pharmacy experienced a tornado. The employees present in the store may or may not be of assistance and  may or may not know where items can be found. The only checkout lanes open late at night are the self checkout lanes-however this allows for a fairly smooth checkout experience. Positive-the only 24 hour grocery and market in town, when the family is sick with the flu and some emergency Theraflu, paper towels and soda is needed, I know I can find it here. That being said-what’s up with the guy in the leopard skin cape running up and down the aisles, the emaciated gentleman pulling an equally emaciated chihuahua (dog dressed as Santa!) in a red wagon through the aisles? One wonders if this store should employ it’s own security (like Target, or Dirt Cheap, or any of the local markets). But it’s a free country I suppose.

name: Lauren
text:
**Update: Surprise! Surprise! I have another bad review for this horrible store. I am beyond irate at this point. I have been getting my prescriptions filled here for years and over the last year it has been a nightmare. Today, I called the pharmacy to get my prescriptions filled, and asked if there were 90 day supplies available by my doctor. She placed me on hold for over 10 minutes, and NEVER CAME BACK. I hung up and called right back, and the pharmacy was CLOSED for lunch. From my previous experience at this pharmacy, I would bet that this was done to me intentionally. EVERY time I go there to pick up prescriptions, the employees are beyond rude, and treat me like I don’t deserve to be served there. These kids are playing with people’s health. The ONLY reason I get my medications filled at Walmart is because I can actually afford them there. I am so angry and disappointed at this situation, but also because I KNOW nothing will change at Walmart. I attempted contacting management today, and they couldn’t even bother to pick up the phone to talk to me. I have also complained to the corporate website to no avail. 🙄🤷🏻‍♀️ WHEN WILL I LEARN? 😩

**update: On 5/20/18 I walked by the fish area and the beta fish CUPS were stacked on top of each other!!!!! I spoke to the manager and informed him the fish could suffocate and die because of this ignorance. I urged him to PROPERLY TRAIN his employees or to stop selling fish. I was so disgusted I couldn’t even shop there. I do have photo proof, but google won’t let me post a picture.

Most employees are rude and have no idea how to answer most questions. Occasionally I’ll run into a friendly employee. My biggest concern is the state of their fish. Walmart should NOT be selling live animals, especially if their employees have no real training on how to care for living creatures.

name: C. Brown
text:
7/22/2016
I absolutely HATED this location because the setup seems backwards and confusing to me. It seems cluttered and discombobulated. Nothing is organized or convenient, which is why I NEVER shop here.

However, I placed an online order which had to be picked up there so I had no choice but to go there yesterday. I was so shocked at the service I received, I had to do a double take at the banner store name.

Walk in the store and head straight to the pick up section. No sooner than I hit the service screen, a woman pops up, greets me and asked if I've been helped, excuses herself and walks to the back. Before the door could shut, Jenn walks out the other door behind the register and greets me with a friendly salutation and asks, "How may I assist you today?" I'm thinking, "Am I actually at Walmart?" I tell her, give her my order number and ID (which she politely requested), she finds the info on her screen, and before walking to the back asks, "Would you like some water while you wait?" As she reaches behind her.

WAIT, WHAT? Did she just offer me water? I decline, she excuses herself to fetch my package and I look behind the counter to see a small fridge. SHE DID offer me water... I had to check the sign to remind myself that I was at Walmart and not some fancy schmancy store.

She brings the order out, confirms it, does whatever she has to while making small talk, I sign for it and I'm out...took less than 7 minutes.

Still in a daze, I walk to Electronics to find the Apple TV thing. Walking through I don't see it. Spot a guy working on something and ask him (Robert, is his name, I think). He quickly, without hesitation, stops whatever he was doing and promptly unlocks a cabinet, all the while greeting me and informing me about the item I've requested.

So now I'm really paranoid, cause he has actual KNOWLEDGE of the item...this has got to be the TWILIGHT ZONE! He rings it up along with my other stuff while chatting away. Everything done, he thanks me for shopping at Walmart (really) and I'm out!

I still don't like this location and wouldn't go back unless by force, but this was a great experience for which I HAD TO write about.

name: Heather Davenport
text:
For the 3rd time in six weeks when I went to the Walmart on Whittlesey to pick up my groceries they were not ready when promised. On two occasions I had to wait until the next day. Today my groceries were to be ready by 9am. I knew they were running behind so I arrived at 11am. I sat in my car with my 8 year old daughter for over an hour before I could get an employee to talk to me and no on would answer my phone. By the time my groceries were brought to my car it was 1:05 pm AND my car battery had died. When I told the Walmart employee that my car battery had died because I had waited so long I received a blank stare and he walked away. Thanks to the kindness of strangers who were also being held hostage waiting for their groceries I was able to get jumped off and on my way after sitting in your parking lot for almost 2 1/2 hours. My advise to you is to communicate clearly and quickly with your customers. Making them wait for over an hour before you even acknowledge them is unacceptable. You had my money and you had my groceries so what choice do I have other than to wait when no one will communicate to me when I should expect my groceries.
I have been a loyal Walmart grocery online customer since the program started in my area last October, check your records. I use this program because I am a working mother of 3 and this allows me to spend more time with my family and less time walking up and down aisle of the grocery store. Well on three occasions now I have waited an hour or more... I could have done the shopping myself. Needless to say I'm done. I was a loyal Winn Dixie customer before online grocery and since it is no longer a reliable, time- saving service I will be headed back to Winn Dixie. I was nice while it lasted but if you continue to conduct business in this manner you will lose more customers than just me.
Best of luck!

Customer ID: 56782149

text: Don't ever take your vehicle to the automotive dept at the wal mart on whittlesey they are not helpful nor are they knowledgeable of their products I called to ask about battery for my truck the sales associate i spoke with said they had a battery in stock that could fit my truck so I called around to other places to get more prices however I eventually called wal mart back bc they had the best price Lori answered the phone I asked her again about the battery and she also told the battery would fit my vehicle I also asked her could they install the battery she said yes I told her I'm on my way I got there at 6 to purchase the battery and have it installed only to be told they could not install it today I would have to come back the next day I told Lori I wish I would have known that I wouldn't have come today so I waited the next day I got there around 815 and was told it would be a 2 hour wait for my battery to be installed so I left my truck there to only be called 3 hours later from a sales associate saying the battery does not fit my truck!!!!!! I was so livid!!! So I returned to wal mart to get a refund and take my services else where I asked the other associate about the battery to only be told it must have been a new person who told me the battery would fit my truck and if was her or lori they knew better I then told her Lori is the one who sold me the battery !!!!! They then took forever to return my money due to no money being in the register then they left the battery that couldn't fit inside my truck !!!!!!!! Needless to say I will never return to this wal mart automotive department for anything again their customer service is horrible !!!!!

text: Some of these employees are SOOOOOOO RUDE! My partner was at the coinstar machine & it took his coins without giving an accurate count. There was a customer service center employee by the name of Virginia Love that came to his aide because she saw it happen too. I walked up as they were on the phone with coinstar customer service, but what blew me was the fact that an employee by the name of VONICE was tasked with helping them solve this issue and she had a horrible attitude about it. She wasn't looking us in the face at all, and when we asked her questions, she'd mumble something and walk away. She wasn't giving us direct answers AT ALL, and she was getting upset with my partner as if it was his fault the machine malfunctioned. She was speaking to Miss Virginia Love SO disrespectfully. it was disgusting how bad her attitude was, ESPECIALLY with how rude she was being to Miss Love, who is visibly older than her. Everyone knows not to disrespect your elders. Miss Love was only trying to help my parter so they would know he wasn't lying. I understand that there is only so much they can do with the coinstar machine without a coinstar vendor present, but VONICE had an attitude from the start. There was another very round woman that came to unlock the machine, she had an attitude as well, but her name tag was flipped over so I couldn't see it. She called my partner "shawty," as if that was professional. she said "scu'me shawty" WHAT? Why is that your preferred choice of communication when interacting with customers? The whole experience was mind blowing. However, I am very appreciative of Miss Virginia Love for all of her support, considering how rude the other employees were. It's quite obvious that Miss Love should've been in a higher position as opposed to VONICE who clearly needs more training. Someone needs to address this.

name: D.C.J. News Media
text:
This store does a pretty good job of it. Been there several times. Most of the people are friendly and helpful.

I notice from store to store they all have their own flavor. You can call it an attitude of helpfulness and just good manners. Some are far better than others.

This store carries a large selection of firearms compared to others in the chain, in fact I've been to several others across America that have had zero because of state laws, or the local community is far left and anti gun.

This is the explanation I have been given by their employees as to why certain stores were absent of arms.

This may or may not be of concern to anyone specific such as a hunter,or sportsman. VS. someone who is not.

This store is cleaner than some stores in the chain. It's a full size store with the standard offerings.

This store also had a drive through Rx at it's side, which I have only seen a few which I think they all should have for disabled folks.

BTW the management here always seem to do pretty good 😊 by folks that I've seen or experienced. I certainly have not found this to be true at most others in the chain.

name: James Barton
text:
Most of the employees in this store are friendly and helpful. There's the occasional poor performer, but that's to be expected with the number of employees they have. Selection is decent, particularly for the size of Andalusia. Prices are what you would expect from Walmart.

Stocking is the problem here. Sometimes the shelves are stocked. Too often they're not. I don't blame the employees. It's got to be a management issue. Maybe there aren't enough people hired to stock the shelves. Or perhaps they're doing other jobs. I end up coming back because there aren't very many options without stopping at 10 different stores, but I feel that a store that actually kept their shelves stocked would put this Walmart in a bind.

text: For as long as I can remember I've always used the Pharmacy in Walmart in Andalusia. Mrs Debbie, the head pharmacist, is an absolute sweetheart. She goes out of her way to help people. However, Walmarts Pharmacy Policies are sickening. They will fill and refill and refill Narcotics. Lortab, Oxy, Narcos, any kind of opiates. No limit, no problem. I use to be able to go in 9-10 times a month with Lortab scripts and get them filled no problem. I have since cleared myself up thanks to my wife and kids. I was put on a Opiate cravings suppressant to stay away from them. Walmart NO LONGER fills any kind of Anti Opiate Dependency medicine. They refuse to fill anything that will get you off of painkillers. I was told by an actual Doctor that They make their money off of Opiates, and any kind of suppressant to help get you off is taking away from them. So they have made a policy on NOT HELPING THOSE IN CRISIS! SORRY! SORRY SORRY SORRY! I will continue spreading this info all the way up the chain. Walmart does not care about you or your problems as long as they get that dollar!

text: Best place on earth! Love this place. I come here 3 or 4 times a day. I enjoy the staff. I enjoy the atmosphere. I love the parking lot. Can't wait to go back tomorrow!

name: Doug Pike
text:
Seems they finally opened up the Garden Center entrance (limited hours). However there is no register open, so you cannot check out there (reason for one less star).

The folks at the Automation Center in Arab Alabama are very helpful. I've purchased two sets of tires in the past few months (two different vehicles). And they have been accommodating to what I needed. Yesterday I was looking for battery for my lawn mower, and the young man pointed me to where they were located with a smile. He had a positive attitude and willingness to help me. After helping me, I heard his eagerness to help the next gentleman waiting for help. Good Job! We need more service like this!

She was very helpful along with the gentlemen that was taking my bags and putting them in my buggy. He came out after me collecting buggys and took mine also. I thank him and drove away but I believe he came back and collected my husband's electric cart. Our whole experience made our day a little brighter.

name: STOKED JL
text: I have to give credit were its due . This wallmart I will gladly give them 5 stars . From the moment I walked in I was greeted at the door . she was friendly and informative. My second experience was with lady at the service desk . she was obviously having a rough morning but she still was extremely nice . I was instantly helped with my transaction and quickly on my way to shopping.  While shopping I observed the cleanliness of the rest of the store and all its facilities. The stock was amazing as well . they had everything I needed and more . when came time for my final check out , there was no line what so ever . I went straight through it was a speedy check out with great friendly service . my over all experience was above and beyond my expectations so I will gladly rate this place with max stars . It is a great family friendly place with amazing helpful workers and I will gladly return next time I need anything.

I had ordered 50 lbs of dog food as part of my order so now I get to go out of my way to go to Walmart and get this myself because they “forgot”. We order at the same time and I pick ours up at Guntersville usually with no complications. We won’t be back to Arab Walmart.

name: Thoehn (Thoehn)
text:
I avoid this place if I can help it. It is true that they have everything in one place and are usually the cheapest on everything except fresh meats and fruit on occasion, but as most mega corporations are prone to do, they exploit their employees for the sake of their bottom line.

I say this from experience, as I used to work for Walmart. They  refuse to pay a living wage, they never keep enough employees on hand - as I am sure many other reviewers have stated, citing the long checkout lines- and what workers they do have on the clock are overworked to the point of hating their job. At least I know I did.

Now that I am no longer an employee but a customer, I see first-hand just how this devotion to nothing but the bottom line affects the public's perceptions of the store. No one WANTS to go to Walmart; we do it because they've pretty much shut down most competition. Cashiers who are already working as hard as they can get blamed for the long lines and if you need assistance, there are hardly enough employees to go around, so you'll likely get some poor guy or gal who isn't even assigned to the department you're needing help with. This usually means that you will be left less than satisfied.

I will give them credit for implementing self-checkout for convenience's sake, but that also means they have even less incentive to keep the front checkouts amply staffed, so it also comes with drawbacks.

text: Worst pharmacy I've ever had experience with. Dropped my daughter's prescription at 3 in the afternoon, because the convenient location, and asked for a text when it was ready. Called at 6 because of no response and the pharmacist told me they hadn't filled one because the request was for chewables and they didn't have that, so I ok'd the pill form. Again told 10 minutes. I showed at 6:30 only to find they didn't have her Medicaid information, so waited another 10 minutes only to find out the doctor hadn't signed the scripts and that they knew this, but I didnt get a phone call, nor did they try to reach the doctor/hospital where it was written. Now I'm told they will call. Waited another 10 minutes only for them to tell me it now has to be filled, so I sat down right in front of them. At 7:10 I got upset and stood in line again. Once I got up there the woman at the counter turned around looking for the scripts only to pull them off of the rack where they had been hanging, who knows how long ago. Then it gets passed for the pharmacist to review and I waited another five minutes because he was nowhere to be found. No customer service and the workers are extremely slow. I'll take prescriptions anywhere but here from now on simply because it will be faster absolutely anywhere in town to drive there and back.

text: I only go here in "emerencies". I don't know if I'll have space for this story so here's the abbreviated version. I have to say 1st that I have always loved Walmart, in general. Cheap prices and they have everything. I won't get into all of the politics of it. I just loved them. Went here at 11:30 pm to get a pre-workout protein bar. Parked, turned off my SUV, (which has heavily tinted windows) and was looking for my headphones. Guy tries to open my passenger front door. I hop out and he immediately bolts and jumps into another vehicle. So far, nothing here is Walmart's fault. Went in to tell the manager that someone is breaking into cars and to call the police. I'll never forget the manager's response. "You'll have to call them yourself. It happens so often that they don't even come when we call them anymore". So, there are times when one of my kids needs diapers or medicine and everything else is closed so I'll go. And there are times during the day when I need something that costs twice as much every where else I've checked so I'll go. But, I never go alone and it's always super quick. Here's the point. It's a Walmart. Just like every other Walmart. But when the employees aren't even willing to go through the trouble of picking up a phone for criminal acts happening on their property, then I'm never going to feel safe with my family at that store. We all know Walmart has cut way back on security in order to cut rising costs (caused in large part by theft). I'm just one person in, what I am assuming is, a sea people that have actually felt the sting of those cutbacks.

name: Rain Davis
text:
This is a continuation of a problem I had with a deep cycle marine battery from the Talladega walmart. I was sent to sylacauga after waiting 5 and a half hours to have a battery tested and returned. Yeah, I admit it was about 20 minutes after the tire/ auto center was supposed to have closed, but I was told by the Talladega employee that a manager at the customer service counter, in sylacauga, would go back and swap out my battery.

So, I mule in this battery to the customer service desk. The cashier told me the auto dept was closed. I replied that a manager was expecting me. Cashier called the customer service manager up, I explained things to her. She said id have to come back tomorrow as well cause they lock up their batteries at night. I asked if anyone in the building had keys. Frustrated she had to do her job, she hops on the phone. Just a few minutes later she yelled across the customer service area, and said I had to follow her.

So I tried, she made sure that she was a good 20' in front of me so she could talk with her coworker without being overheard. Im a disabled veteran. I have to pick and choose when I can hurry, and after hauling this heavy battery around for the better part of a day, I was all out of get up and go. And I especially don't care for your small town, holyer- than- thou attitude cause you "have to turn a key". It's called doing your job.

Anyways, so I make my way back to the battery area. The manager there went on to state several reasons he couldn't do the exchange. From me not having a receipt (handed it to him, with the last exchange receipt) to the battery being old (the color coded sticker dates it back to November of 2018), and finally the managers settled on being unable to do the exchange because the computer says it's already been exchanged. That's 100%, I traded the last box of garbage for this one.

I'll be calling corporate after lunchtime today.

Summation: the employees are killing this big box store. Don't visit Talladega or Sylacauga. They are both garbage and could care less about the customer.

name: Cindy Mauldin
text: People with overflowing carts are allowed to go thru self-service cash registers at the Sylacauga, Al Walmart, causing those of us with 20 or less items to have to wait and wait forever. I have witnessed a lot of theft due to this reckless Walmart procedure. There is no way that any Walmart employees can monitor these thiefs, and also assist others who have computer issues at the self-service registers. There is absolutely NO REASON for a customer to have a cart full of one hundred items of clothes and food, to ever be in the self-service lines. There is not space to accommodate so many items. There must be a limit of NO MORE THAN 25 ITEMS AT SELF-SERVICE REGISTERS. ALL OTHERS MUST BE RE-DIRECTED TO CASH REGISTERS WITH WALMART ATTENDANTS. Doing so will reduce Walmart theft, reduce costs to customers caused by theft, and will allow lines at self- service registers to move quickly, which is the purpose for self-service in the first place. I have seen a husband with one cart and his wife with a second cart, with 6-packs of drinks dangling over the top of carts. This practice must be stopped by Wal-Mart. Intentional theft is the only reason people bring overloaded carts to self- service registers. Walmart needs to stop being blind!!!!

name: Meesha Telvanni
text: Veggies aren't really fresh or neat. Zucchini  was crammed in so tight you couldn't get any without scraping the others up. Meat area hasn't had a good selection in awhile. Never anyone in the bakery. Many food items on the shelves had no price, and items all mixed up so I didn't know which price was which all through grocery area. A bag of sugar substitute I put in my buggy had a hole in it, got all over my foods and the floor. I asked someone for help so there wouldn't be a mess, and they sighed and said, "what do you want me to just get the bag from you?" So, I went no, I'd like a broom so no one slips on it. Person said they'd get someone. The new person came and was very sweet and cleaned up the mess and asked if I needed a new bag. The cashier didn't ring a lot of my veggies as what they were, even when I told her. For example, I had a ton of poblanos, and she rang them as 3 g peppers. My bag of cherries I weighed at around $8, never made it on my receipt. So somehow they didn't get scanned. Free food not a problem for most, but I buy for several ppl, and need the items on the receipt. So, I gave it a three cause it made shopping from a list very frustrating. I left and went to another store to finish getting what I needed.

name: Ryan Cass
text: This Walmart location used to be my family’s go to for quick shopping but over the years the staff and service have become less helpful. The store is more dirty and disorganized than other locations in the area and there’s several items every other Walmart I go to has but this location always seems to be out of stock so that’s why I had to dock them 3 stars. I’d bump my score up if they would take the time to remodel the store a bit and better train the staff and bump up the inventory.

name: Mary Baldwin
text: This store doesn't appear to be very handicapped/disabled friendly. They have plenty of handicap parking but as far as someone with a disability being able to go in store and shop that's where they apparently have no concern about. If you have/bring your own mobile cart you will be able to shop..however if you don't you may want to use the services of another store because you will be unable to get around the store to shop. I was there tonight and they only had 3 carts in the store. The two on the side which the doors were opened didn't work at all and the third one, which was on the other end of the store on the closed doors side,  wasn't charged nor was it even plugged in to charge the battery.. I asked an employee who was bringing in carts on the closed side if they maybe had a cart outside that hadn't been brought in by chance. He told me he would go get me one and walked away.. After waiting 10 minutes I proceeded to head back to the other side I had originally came in hoping to catch him headed back. Well no such luck he was no where to be seen. Not only that but while I was on my way there I notice two teen girls ( that definitely had nothing wrong and no need to use) playing around the store with each other on two.. Meanwhile the store had myself needing one and gentleman needing one for his wife so we could shop!! I left the store and went elsewhere to do business. text: Visited on my normal Friday evening shopping trip  at around 6:45.  The only regular register that was open was the tobacco lane which was backed up with probably 6 or 7 customers with shopping carts. I will use the self checkout when I have small amounts so today I got in that line for the self checkout corral. After waiting in line for several minutes and making to that front the young lady says "cards only" I tell her I'm paying in cash and she tells me "I guess you will have to go get in the other lines" and turns away. So we go to one of the self checkout with the belts and when we make it there it too says 'card only'. Next we try customer service but there is a customer having trouble with a return and they turn the lights out on us so we finally go to the tobacco line. Probably should have done that to begin with. So on the way out I call the 1800walmart number to complain her answer was the cash shortage that happened a few months ago or she said "at least that's what they tell me". I'm sure it was someone that has to count down the cash from the self checkout at night decided they wanted to leave early so they pulled all the cash and switched the registers to card only. This has happened on a few occasions at this store. It was once the cleaner and better stocked walmarts but has suffered for the past few years. On the way home my wife and I made the decision to drive the extra mile and start shopping at Target again.

name: Susan DuPre'
text: Grocery Pick-up service.  I shopped online on a Saturday afternoon, scheduled my pick-up for Sunday 12-1 slot, paid online, received online confirmation that my order had been received and would be ready at the time slot I had selected.  On Sunday, I arrived at 12:15 and saw 3 other cars waiting in the designated spots for pick-up.  When I pushed to red button to let the crew know of my arrival, they sounded confused and told me "we'll work it out."  About 10 minutes later, an employee came out to my car and very humbly apologized that my order and the one for the man in the truck next to me had not been noticed, but that they would get the man's order out, then mine would be next, as quickly as they could.  Fifteen minutes after that, the employee pushed the man's order out to his car, unloaded it, and proceeded to have a TWENTY minute discussion with that customer!!!  They were hidden from my view by the man's massive truck, but I could hear them talking - just in regularly toned voices, no yelling or sounds of anyone upset - couldn't hear what they were saying, however.  When the employee finally went back inside the store, it was another 10 minutes before he got my order out to my car!  He again very humbly apologized and blamed the man in the truck for "needing to talk about something".  At this time, I had been waiting almost an HOUR!  I could have gone inside and done my own shopping, then been back out to my car by then!  I was NOT happy, as  it was lunchtime, and my whole family was at home texting me and asking when I would be home with the groceries for lunch!  This service sounds like a convenient option, but in my case, it wasted a lot of my time!  I'm not sure I'll use this service again if I risk having my order overlooked.  I don't have that kind of time!

name: Stephen Madrid
text: I have never been treated with as much disrespect as the tire center workers treated my wife and I at this Walmart.  I ordered her new tires online, and after putting them on my wife immediately noticed that one was losing air pressure.  She returned to the tire center and was told she probably ran over a nail and it happens “all the time” to new tires.  There was no nail and they inspected the tire and filled it with air and sent her on her way.  She immediately noticed it was still losing air pressure and returned a third time with me.  They took the tire off and returned and told her they could not repair it, there was a small cut in the side wall of the tire… and it was not their problem.  After several heated discussions they told us we would have to order a new tire and there was nothing they could do.  Never have I seen a lack of care for customers like this.  We will never use this store again!

name: Captain Velveeta

Otherwise, there wouldn't be so many empty shelves.  The largest retailer in the world doesn't even know how to manage inventory.  PITIFUL display of management. Absolutely pitiful.

Plus I was in the store 45 minutes before Closing time so employees we're restocking or cleaning. Not  bothered by that. There was no greeter at the door and I had forgotten my mask, something I had never done before. I proceeded anyways past the entry because I had observed other  Walmart's providing courtesy disposable masks to assist customers without one. I checked the sanitizing station only to find there were no masks and no employees close by. In my purse  I located a suitable facial covering to use in the store.  Employees  I  encountered did not acknowledge me or offer assistance when trying to find items.  Also,  I had trouble reaching items on the top shelves pushed to the back of the Shelves.  I had to be creative to get those items because I was unable to locate anyone to assist me. Additionally the main aisle from the back to front of the store was blocked by furniture in boxes. After getting my groceries I went to the only open registers , self check-out. Next to my register an employee stood as I check my items out. Before I completed the transaction that employee walked away and began cleaning the other registers. No smile, no acknowledgement nor was I spoken to. Not by anyone through this entire visit. Kind of sad people working there seemed like they were very unhappy :(

Forced to check out almost $200 of groceries in the self checkout. Only two cashiers working tonight at 6:30 pm on a Saturday. One was expressed checkout and the regular checkout was backed up with 12 customers and all of them had full shopping carts. A customer complained to the yellow vest at the customer service area and no action was taken initially. Customer: "You know you are going to lose business over this!" Yellow vest: "I know mam" (said in a dismissive tone).

Initially I thought the self checkout was a good thing, but now I see if there is no choice, it is a bad thing.

There are only 10 checkout Lanes in this Walmart now and the rest are self checkout.

If I am going to be forced to scan and bag my own groceries, then I would like an employee discount.

Avoid this store at all costs.

Update 10/25/2020

Moved from one star to zero now. The store is constantly out of stock on most items and not even worth wasting time to drive here.

name: starla hodo
text:
The customer service is awful. I needed to print pictures out for my sons graduation party. I needed help with the kiosk. Looked around to see if I could find an employee.
No one in sight. It took me an hour in that one department. Got my picture printed and got my ticket to pay for my pictures. I also have other items in my grocery cart I need to pay for.
Go to the front to look for a someone to check me out. All the registers with a cashier is back 2-3 deep. May I add that there was really not that many cashiers working. It was all scan and go! The scan and go is ridiculous!! If I’m checking myself out, I need a discount. Not everyone was made for checking yourself out. Most all of the scan and go were full. Well I found a scan and go open. Found this lady with a yellow vest on and ask about paying for my pictures. She tells me I will need to go to the back to the photo department to pay for them. I said okay, I’ll check myself out and then I will go pay. So I proceeded to check myself out. Well unfortunately I had a item that didn’t have a price tag. So what do you do? Is there some way I can call for a price check? Nope! So I proceeded to look around for help. Found someone in a yellow vest. She called some other guy in a yellow vest. She stands there in my way of checking myself out looking for a price on something  for another customer. Anyway, the guy ask me where I got the 2019 item. I said, in the back. Then he said, I don’t know the price on this item.  I said, that’s fine I will just leave that here and not get that item.
Finished my self checkout. Go to the back to pay for my pictures. Walk back there and they are changing out the register. The lady says I can check you out in the back. Looks at my pictures and tells me I need a copyright to the picture I took of my sons graduation picture.  She said I can’t give you this picture. So already irritated from my whole trip and wondering were this lady was the hour I had sit here looking for help. I said, that’s fine. Shred those, that’s fine. I just want to pay for the other pictures. She looks at me like I’m crazy. I said the ones you have in your hand. I have several pictures there that doesn’t have a copyright. I want to pay for those.
I have never complained about any store or any customer service.
Your customer service is terrible! Scan and go is ridiculous! If I am checking myself out, I should get a discount. A few scan and go is a good idea for a few items. But turning most of the store into scan and go Is a inconvenience for customers. I can’t believe how much Walmart has went down hill.

text: Auto Center is a joke!!!! Was told it would be less than a hour to put on 1 new tire. I said that's fine, I've got some shopping to do. I shopped slowly, and checked up on my vehicle at about the 1 hour mark. It was just being pulled into the bay.  No problem... I had yet to get my cold items, and decided to go ahead, do that, and check out. (cause how long could it possibly take to take off 1 old tire and put another on?) Well let me tell y'all.  Another whole hour! I still kept my cool. Paid for the work, and headed outside as they were pulling it out of the bay, I looked at the vehicle and they had put the new tire on the drivers front, instead of drivers rear!!!!! Common sense should have told someone that the drivers front had no need for changing. It had 90% tread opposed to the rear tire. He said, someone must have wrote it up wrong. You think??? So right back to where we started, except now he has to put my other tire back on... In the process, he managed to mess up the balance on everything.  Had to get Warrior Tire to do a rotate and balance to get me straight once it was all said and done. The two tires that Walmart AUTOMOTIVE touched, managed to be off 1.5 ounces on the front and 3 ounces off in the rear. He also filled my rear tire with 40lbs of air! Wrong!!!! Never take your vehicle to this location! Like the old commercial says, EVERYTHING IS RIDING ON YOUR TIRES! I filed a complaint and never heard a thing from them, and it's been almost 3 weeks! I wouldn't have any customer's if I ran my business like this!

name: Howler Wolf
text:
This is the worst stocked Walmart I have ever seen. And it is consistently understocked. What's funny about that is that they run out of stuff that isn't common items, there are always people stocking day and night, and they can be out of an item for over a month (with me checking every week for over a month).

To list a few of uncommon items they were out of for over a month is tarter powder in the baking section and evening primrose oil in vitamins. There is absolutely no way that for over a month every bottle of tarter powder was bought up. And I don't mean at Christmas time, I'm talking about in June they are out of spices. Ridiculous. The manager or the ordering system doesn't do its job properly. That's the only reason why these things would consistently be out of stock.

Workers are always stocking items which means they have pallets of items all over the floor even at rush hours when people are getting off of work. The floor itself has too many floor displays which makes it really hard to navigate around them and the large amount of people that tend to be there.

There is also a huge lack of items regardless of what department you are looking in. The kids clothes is always understocked and has horrible selection. The home section with pots and pans is always lacking anything you could possibly be looking for. I literally couldn't find a basic set of salt and pepper shakers. I've even had to search for basic toothpaste because they were out of all Colgate.

When it's time for school shopping, the aisles that contain those items are very clutter and disorganized. You can never find anything. And even when it's not school shopping time, there is still a lack of items where you can find them.

The electronics section sucks as well. If you are looking for a particular item, they never have it. Period. I even struggled a few months ago to find usb drives. Seriously.

The meat department never has the cuts of meat I need, even down to the kind of ground beef I buy.

The whole store is barely worthwhile to go to.

The only reason I shop here is because it's the only store in the area unless you want to pay triple the price at Publix. This Walmart is more like a Dollar General when it comes to availability of items. The only reason this store succeeds is because no other store has moved into the area. Fingers crossed that we'll get a Super Target or something in the next few years.

For clothes and any kind of real shopping I drive to the Walmart in Trussville. It's well worth the drive because they are very organized and the selection is always great.

name: Shilo J
text:
I don’t like to give a single star unless the entire experience was extremely horrendous enough for me to have words with management (which is rare),nor do I give out a fifth star unless I’m wowed enough to “knock my socks off”(which is extremely rare). That being said, the only thing keeping me from giving them a different is for these reasons:

1.)  a single star rating is whenever I’ve had an issue, they fixed the problem to make things right. It didn’t matter if we did online ordering or in-store shopping, it was corrected by whichever one handled the original order.

2.) a 2-star rating because the last 3 or 4 times I’ve been to the store the cashiers were wearing genuine smiles and greeted me when I came up to their lane, were friendly and held a pleasant conversation while they worked, bagged my groceries the way they should’ve been bagged, and seemed like they were there to work and not just be there for a paycheck. The cashier lanes weren’t overly packed. The last 2 or 3 times I was there, the staff stalking shelves asked me if they could help me with something rather than me having to ask them for help or me walking away frustrated which was actually pleasant for a change. The staff that I did ask for help from were awesome too. Both sets of stalkers went the extra mile and did what any person in the customer service industry should do for a customer.

Thank you to those wonderful individuals who worked the last few times I’ve been to the store. You guys were awesome and WalMart should have more people like you! Keep up the excellent work!

Overall, what keeps them from getting either a negative star rating (if only it were possible) or even a 4-5 star rating is for reasons listed above. Especially since 9 out of 10 times they are out of the majority of everything, they are massively understaffed, most of the employees are rude and can be even ruder if they feel you are a nuisance when asking for help or interrupting their personal phone conversations, you can’t get through most of the aisles because there’s pallets of stock everywhere, and when we order online the store substitutes items that either is nowhere remotely close to the ordered item or doesn’t use their noggins and give the correct item from their shelves because the item became out of stock online (which means staff if you have it on your shelves, even if the online item says “out of stock”, substitute the same exact item from your shelf and not something entirely different), or they gave my order away to another individual. Yes I know you have the option to reject items but when you go into the store and find the exact same item you ordered on the shelf it kind of irks a person off, especially if it happens more oft than not. There has to be a line drawn somewhere because patience one’s behalf and ignorance on another’s only goes so far.
For the record, it was explained to me this way:  when you do your shopping online their stock is a separate entity from the actual store’s stock. In other words if it’s out of stock online it doesn’t necessarily mean it’s out of stock in the store.

text: Went in yesterday to purchase a gift card. American Express for $25. I only had my credit card on me so couldn't buy it. No biggie. Came back today with my DEBIT card and the girl (young African American girl with fake glasses on register 23 at 11:40 am 5/17/16) rang my first few things up and then proceeded to ring the American Express gift card separately. I swiped my card, it asked if I wanted cash, I said no, she pressed a button and it said I had to use another card. She walks away and comes back and tells me I have to have a debit card. I tell her that IS my debit card and she argues with me that it isn't. First off, I know which cards are which since they are mine. Secondly, she was pressing a button to make it credit because it never asked for my pin. She rang it up again and so I swiped my card, again. Same thing: cash back? No, she presses button, "use another form of payment". Then she gets an attitude with me and is snippy trying to tell me I'm "obviously paying with credit because it would accept debit". No, I'm paying with my freakin DEBIT card that I JUST USED ON MY PREVIOUS ITEMS! I gave her the card back and left. I'll spend my money elsewhere. I'm done coming in this Walmart. Every time I have lately I've been met with rude employees who think I owe them something to ring my items up or help me locate something. It is ridiculous. Mr. Jeff jay, you need to get a handle on your employees because I am not the first, nor last, who has had these experiences.

The lights dim at 10:15 PM, And someone comes over the intercom rushing you to go to the front of the store to check out, the store is closing. No matter if it’s 6 PM or 10pm, there is only one lane that Has someone to check you out and that’s for the tobacco and other products. Every else is directed to go to the self check out In that small area, no matter if you Have a buggy full of groceries or large items. The self checkout for people with a lot of items is lit up, but chained off so it’s unavailable. Doesn’t matter if there are two to three other Employees to help the one attendant that is overseeing the self checkout, The other to talk to each other not directing any attention to the customers, cleaning or loss prevention. Daytime is a lot better if you want to go. No matter what time of day I go in, the dairy section is always very well stocked and clean. Electronics has alot of options, just needs to be aware of that advertisement posted is something that Walmart honors, if not take it down.

My son said that he said Hi and the man whispered stuff to him but my son said he could not understand him. My son said this freaked him out. My husband and other family saw this man interact with my son as they were walking up so they got over to him. The man walked off out of site quickly. When I returned few seconds later they told me. I walked all around trying to find this man and did not see him/anyone matching his description. I do not know if it was innocent man just there and my son misunderstood him or if this man had bad intentions. Just be aware parents unfortunately you never know anymore with folks. Its sad. They refused to open the door because it was a directive from the headquarters. I had to walk all the way to the end of the building where the exit was and then all the way back to my car. text:
The Jasper Wal-Mart is undergoing reconstruction and is a little harder to get around in. Things are also not where they were before. I don't like change any more than you do, but I can live with it if it means the store will be easier to shop in. It will definitely be better aesthetically. I hope it will be set up better for the consumer. I'm sure, however, that the main reason is to make people pass things they wouldn't normally go by so you will have a chance to see things you normally wouldn't look at.
As for the staff, they were all very busy and didn't stop to help unless approached by the customer. They did stop and help once asked and took their time with the people who asked for help. I know they will be happy once construction is finished. Just the noise is loud enough to drive you crazy. At least give them the benefit of the doubt. The noise is excruciatingly loud. Overall a better than average shopping experience.

name: Macie Hughes
text:
I’m not one to do reviews too often, especially not on Walmart. BUT I just have to say I wish I could Give more than 5 stars to the grocery pick up department. Earlier this week I had placed an order to be picked up Wednesday after I got off work. Wednesday morning I had some things come up and was so worried it would be a pain to call and get the order cancelled and get my money back... let me just say - I talked to a few people through out the day Alex & Zach I think were 2 of the ones helping me. They were the absolute nicest WalMart employees I’ve ever spoken with. They were so understanding and polite. They even called me later in the afternoon to confirm my order had been cancelled & the money would be back in my account in 2-3 business days.
I wish all WalMart employees had the same attitude as these guys! Definitely can not wait to hopefully work with them again! Not enough positive ever gets posted on businesses so I wanted to make sure to brag on the pick up department. Thank you both so much for all of your help!!!

text: I just left the jasper Walmart pretty upset. I needed to get into the fitting rooms and so did another lady that came up before me. She had asked a girl that had walked up behind the counter if she could get in the fitting rooms and that girl paged another woman to come open them. This older worker came around just straight up complaining how she couldn’t get her dept done and didn’t have time to stay at the fitting rooms all day. She kept complaining and pretty much made the other woman upset enough to not even want to try on her clothes. The Walmart worker had made the woman feel like she was an inconvenience and I work in retail at a place where customer service is held to high expectations so it made me mad to see the customer treated that way. Even if you are upset you don’t say it in front of customers. Secondly after I debated about mentioning something to the woman I asked if there would be anyone over here tonight to which she decided to point out a sign that I could clearly read and insult my intelligence and said you have to come find us. I didn’t ask her if someone would be over there bc I needed to try on more clothes I asked bc someone else needed to cover this area that was more polite and even if I hadn’t of already known what the sign said you don’t just point at it you explain to the customer that no one stays over there after a certain time and that you will be over in whatever area if they need you. I have to deal with rude customers on a daily basis so when I go to a place I shouldn’t have to deal with rude employees!

name: Dj Moats-Herron
text: The Jasper, Alabama Walmart is just horrible.  There is no other way to describe them.   I'm a huge Walmart fan and I've never had a single complaint about any other store.  With this store, I have nothing but complaints.  The photography department is the worse.  I have trouble getting my own photos developed there, because they are continuously falsely accusing them of being professionally done.  I can request them from the Walmart website and have them delivered without question or harrasment.  They purposefully denied an enlargement for a wedding gift.  The photo had two men getting married in it, so I question the employees reasoning for not allowing the enlargement.  Throughout the years, I've complained to management.  But management does not care and never wants to hear it.  They will not back their prices.  One time, they had a display of socks marked at one price and at the register I was charged another.  When I noted it to the manager, she just rudely ripped off the pricing sign, charged us the higher cost, and seemed more upset about me having some perceived audacity of complaining.  The list of my complaints goes on and on and on.  This place definitely needs new managers and definitely better help in the photography area.  The service is in general extremely rude, extremely pompus, and extremely unhelpful!

name: Juan Cepero
text: Great Local golf shop here in Dothan. I recently purchased a used left handed Cobra F8 driver and I love it. I'm new to golf so a driver was the last thing I was missing. The whole staff was very helpful and attentive. Really great group of folks.

name: Eric King
text: Staff is very helpful. Much better store than you would expect to have in Dothan.

name: Jerome Vascocu
text: These folks have a surprisingly great inventory and are the most helpful and attentive I’ve ever come across. The best “local” golf store atmosphere out there. Never been disappointed!

name: Timra Cloud
text: Quick, helpful and knowledgeable staff.  So glad they're locally available.

name: Norman Clark
text: Fantastic store proving good quality products, fittings and repairs.  Extremely knowledgeable staff on all things golf!!

name: Dp01
text: Best golf shop in town.  Been coming here for years and I’ve never had a bad experience.  If you need new clubs, gear or need work done on existing clubs, this is the only place you should go.  Everyone is always friendly.  Great selection and sales are good too.  Support local golf shops!

name: Umar Abdul-Hakeem
text:
I stopped in GolfPlus Dothan yesterday after visiting the store on Thursday. I had the best experience in 20 plus years of playing golf and having a few fittings in the past.

The young man Mark Krystyn was a superstar, when it comes to professionalism and product knowledge. He gave me an iron fitting and had me walking out of the store very satisfied. The only problem I had with the entire session was that it had to end.

Living in Florida was the only reason that I did not pull the trigger on the purchase, and Mark never pressured me to purchase, what he did say is because you live in Jacksonville Fl area (4 hours away) if I am not satisfied with wanting to purchase the irons in Jacksonville he can order the irons and have them delivered to me.

I told him, my issue is if I need something done To the clubs the distance is to far from my residence.

Top notch Fitter and Organization. KUDOS to Mr. Watson for having Mark on the team.

Umar Abdul-Hakeem

name: Jamie Gilmore
text: I purchased my set of Cleveland irons from here a few years back and couldn’t be happier with them. Also recently  got my putter regripped there. Best shop in the wiregrass in my opinion, don’t waste your time anywhere else. Everyone there is super nice, extremely knowledgeable, and no pressure environment. Everything you are looking for in a positive golf shop experience. Huge variety on golf gear and accessories and good trade in values.

name: Dave King
text: Excellent service from the most knowledgeable staff in the area, I go nowhere else for golf gear. Highly recommended

name: Green Beret1998
text: I stopped in today to purchase a few golf grips and a new 3 Wood Headcover. The store looks amazing and the staff was super friendly and answered all my questions! Super Awesome golf shop!! Mark was so helpful! A+++

name: Jerry Clark
text: Great service from Alan and his staff every time I visit. Always honest and no pressure on buying something not needed. Service on repairs and customization is the best in the area.

name: Rodney Reynolds
text: Professional, polite, knowledgeable and courteous.  Always make the customer feel welcomed.  They did an awesome getting a club repaired for me when I first started out golfing.  I always visit the shop when I come home.
